WEBVTT

00:02.570 --> 00:03.736
ED:
OKAY, LOSER BUYS THE COFFEE.

00:03.738 --> 00:05.070
SAM:
YOU'RE ON.

00:07.208 --> 00:08.407
<i> ED:</i>
<i> ALL RIGHT.</i>

00:08.409 --> 00:09.508
(GUNS CLICK)

00:13.447 --> 00:14.546
(BOOMING GUNSHOT)

00:14.548 --> 00:15.614
SAM:
ONE.

00:16.484 --> 00:17.683
(BOOMING GUNSHOT)

00:17.685 --> 00:18.751
ED:
ONE.

00:20.654 --> 00:22.321
(BOOMING GUNSHOT)

00:22.323 --> 00:23.389
SAM:
TWO.

00:23.391 --> 00:27.326
ED:
YOU REMEMBER HOW
I TAKE MY COFFEE, RIGHT?

00:27.328 --> 00:28.460
(BOOMING GUNSHOT)

00:28.462 --> 00:29.628
TWO.

00:29.630 --> 00:30.696
(GUN CLICKS)

00:37.038 --> 00:38.270
(BOOMING GUNSHOT)

00:38.272 --> 00:39.338
AGH!

00:42.543 --> 00:44.309
ED:
(HEART POUNDS)

00:47.281 --> 00:48.647
(BREATHES HEAVILY)

00:50.451 --> 00:51.450
(BOOMING GUNSHOT)

00:51.452 --> 00:52.518
(WET SPLASH)

00:53.621 --> 00:54.686
(GASPS)

00:57.558 --> 00:59.358
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> NICE SHOT!</i>

01:00.428 --> 01:01.527
(ECHOING GUNSHOT)

01:01.529 --> 01:03.362
SAM:
YOU OKAY?

01:03.364 --> 01:04.563
ED:
YEAH, I JUST...

01:04.565 --> 01:07.566
I JUST COULDN'T GET
MY BREATH THERE.

01:07.568 --> 01:11.236
SAM:
THAT'S 'CAUSE YOU SHOT
IN THAT WIND.

01:12.173 --> 01:13.405
ED:
OKAY, SO COFFEE.

01:14.341 --> 01:16.141
SAM:
YEAH, DOUBLE-DOUBLE,
YOU BET.

01:18.779 --> 01:21.680
(OVERLAPPING SOUND
OF DOGS BARKING)

01:22.616 --> 01:24.383
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

01:25.553 --> 01:27.719
(SOUND OF MULTIPLE
CELL PHONES RINGING)

01:27.721 --> 01:28.787
MAN:
(SHALLOW, UNEVEN BREATHS)

01:28.789 --> 01:31.857
<i> MAN'S ECHOING VOICE:</i>
<i> YOU ARE VALUABLE TO ME</i>
<i> OUT HERE, </i>

01:31.859 --> 01:34.193
<i> AND YOU WOULDN'T WANNA KNOW</i>
<i> WHAT HAPPENS </i>

01:34.194 --> 01:36.528
<i> IF YOU TALK TO THE POLICE</i>
<i> ABOUT THIS CONVERSATION. </i>

01:36.530 --> 01:39.765
(DISTORTED SOUND
OF CHILDREN CRYING)

01:41.735 --> 01:43.585
<i> ECHOING FEMALE VOICE:</i>
<i> (LOUD GASP)</i>

01:43.586 --> 01:45.436
MAN:
(ERRATIC BREATHING,
WHIMPERS PANICKED)

01:45.439 --> 01:47.539
(FLAME CATCHES,
FIRE ROARS AND CRACKLES)

01:47.541 --> 01:50.709
(DISTORTED SOUND
OF POLICE SIRENS)

01:51.645 --> 01:52.878
(DISTORTED SOUNDS
OF LIQUID POURING)

01:52.880 --> 01:54.713
(PANICKED GASPS)

01:54.715 --> 01:57.416
(DISTORTED KNOCKING SOUNDS)

01:57.418 --> 01:59.184
(SOUND OF MULTIPLE
CELL PHONES RINGING)

02:01.255 --> 02:03.322
(GASPING FOR AIR)

02:03.323 --> 02:05.390
ECHOING MALE VOICE:
I KNOW LAINIE SUMMERS.

02:05.392 --> 02:07.376
<i> IF YOU EVER WANNA</i>
<i> SEE HER AGAIN...</i>

02:07.377 --> 02:09.361
<i> WOMAN'S ECHOING VOICE:</i>
<i> (LAUGHS)</i>
<i> OH, ELLIOT!</i>

02:20.641 --> 02:24.243
(KEYBOARD KEYS CLICK,
ELECTRONIC BEEPS)

02:25.379 --> 02:28.714
THIS IS A MESSAGE
FOR LAINIE SUMMERS.

02:28.716 --> 02:30.649
LAINIE...
(TEARFUL SNIFF)

02:30.651 --> 02:32.451
BY THE TIME YOU SEE THIS...

02:32.453 --> 02:35.854
UM, I DON'T KNOW WHAT TO SAY.
I'M SORRY?

02:36.790 --> 02:38.624
BUT I WANTED TO THANK YOU
FOR BEING SO PATIENT WITH ME

02:38.626 --> 02:40.626
AND SUCH A GOOD FRIEND...

02:41.695 --> 02:43.562
BUT I CAN'T HANDLE THIS.

02:43.564 --> 02:44.897
MAN'S ECHOING VOICE:
I'M SURE YOU WOULDN'T WANT
TO SEE HER GET HURT.

02:46.734 --> 02:49.334
ALL I CAN TELL YOU
IS THERE'S NO OTHER WAY.

02:49.336 --> 02:50.869
I KNOW YOU'RE THE ONLY ONE
WHO CAN UNDERSTAND

02:50.871 --> 02:52.771
WHY I HAVE TO DO THIS.

02:56.677 --> 02:59.545
(TEARFUL)
I'M SO SORRY, LAINIE.

03:04.785 --> 03:07.519
(DOOR OPENS)

03:07.521 --> 03:08.754
LAINIE:
HI, HOW ARE YOU?

03:08.756 --> 03:09.755
MAN:
GOOD.

03:09.757 --> 03:10.706
LAINIE:
ARE WE GOOD FOR TODAY?

03:10.707 --> 03:11.656
MAN:
YES, YES, I HAVE THE RESULTS...

03:11.659 --> 03:13.725
(CAMERA CLICKS, BEEPS)

03:13.727 --> 03:14.893
(PHONE KEYS BEEP)

03:15.829 --> 03:17.496
(ELECTRONIC BEEP)

03:35.349 --> 03:36.949
AARON:
(QUIETLY) NOT A SOUND.
YOU SEE THE GUN?

03:36.951 --> 03:38.550
YOU'LL BE SHOT
IF YOU TRY ANYTHING.

03:38.552 --> 03:39.785
ARE WE CLEAR?

03:39.787 --> 03:41.720
I'LL GIVE YOU INSTRUCTIONS
AS WE GO.

03:41.722 --> 03:43.789
WALK!

03:43.791 --> 03:45.174
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SO, SAM SAID THAT, UH,</i>

03:45.175 --> 03:46.558
YOU WENT TO YOUR DAD'S PLACE
THIS MORNING,

03:46.560 --> 03:47.759
HAD A LITTLE ROUND OF "GOLF"?

03:47.761 --> 03:49.228
ED:
YEAH.

03:49.229 --> 03:50.696
YEAH, HE SAID YOU MADE
A PRETTY SWEET SHOT.

03:50.698 --> 03:54.233
THE WIND WAS AT, WHAT, FORTY
WITH A THREE O'CLOCK CROSSWIND?

03:54.235 --> 03:56.535
YOU MAKE A SHOT LIKE THAT,
USUALLY WE CAN'T SHUT YOU UP.

03:56.537 --> 03:57.769
ED:
GREG, THERE'S NO STORY HERE,
ALL RIGHT?

03:57.771 --> 03:59.621
IT WAS A DAMN GOLF BALL.

03:59.622 --> 04:01.472
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> COME ON, EDDIE.</i>
<i> COME ON, WHAT'S GOIN' ON?</i>

04:02.910 --> 04:05.244
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> 911, WHAT IS YOUR EMERGENCY?</i>

04:05.246 --> 04:06.678
<i> CARLA:</i>
<i> THERE'S A MAN TRYING </i>
<i> TO BREAK IN ACROSS THE STREET.</i>

04:06.680 --> 04:07.746
23 DITTMAR.

04:08.882 --> 04:09.748
(SHATTERING CRASH)

04:09.750 --> 04:10.849
HE'S GOING IN.

04:10.851 --> 04:12.768
OH MY GOD,
HE'S GOT A GUN!

04:12.769 --> 04:14.686
(HOT CALL KLAXON BLARES)
TEAM, 911 ON A POSSIBLE
HOME INVASION.

04:14.688 --> 04:15.887
<i> 23 DITTMAR.</i>

04:15.889 --> 04:17.823
CONFIRMED -
ONE ARMED SUBJECT.

04:17.825 --> 04:20.859
<i> ED:</i>
<i> WINNIE, WE'RE ON IT.</i>
<i> (KLAXON WAILS)</i>

04:20.861 --> 04:21.960
AARON:
ALL THE WAY TO THE END.

04:21.962 --> 04:24.396
LAINIE:
(BREATHES RAPIDLY)

04:25.699 --> 04:27.032
<i> SECURITY GUARD:</i>
<i> (LAUGHS)</i>

04:27.033 --> 04:28.366
<i> NO, IT TURNED OUT</i>
<i> TO BE SOME STUDENTS</i>

04:28.369 --> 04:30.535
<i> JUST PLAYING A PRANK.</i>

04:31.472 --> 04:34.373
<i> YEAH,</i>
<i> I GAVE THEM A WARNING.</i>

04:36.744 --> 04:39.478
(LAINIE SHOUTS, PUNCHES,
AARON GRUNTS IN PAIN)

04:39.480 --> 04:41.580
LAINIE:
(SHRIEKS) HELP!

04:41.582 --> 04:42.648
HELP!

04:44.418 --> 04:47.819
SECURITY GUARD:
CODE WHITE! I NEED BACKUP!

04:47.821 --> 04:49.888
WINNIE:
TEAM ONE,
WE GOT ANOTHER HOT CALL.

04:49.890 --> 04:51.857
<i> ATTEMPTED ABDUCTION,</i>
<i> U OF T.</i>

04:51.859 --> 04:52.824
(ALARM SOUNDS)
I CAN RE-UP TEAM TWO.

04:52.826 --> 04:54.293
YEAH, HOLD OFF ON THAT,
WINNIE.

04:54.295 --> 04:55.727
<i> SAM, SPIKE,</i>
<i> WHAT'S YOUR POSITION?</i>

04:55.729 --> 04:56.745
WE'RE ALMOST AT THE HOUSE.

04:56.746 --> 04:57.762
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> WE'RE JUST ARRIVING, BOSS.</i>

04:57.765 --> 04:59.315
ALL RIGHT,
YOU STAY ON IT.

04:59.316 --> 05:00.866
WINNIE, WE'LL TAKE
THE UNIVERSITY CALL.

05:00.868 --> 05:02.734
KEEP TEAM TWO ON STANDBY.

05:02.736 --> 05:03.735
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> COPY.</i>

05:03.737 --> 05:04.803
(SIREN WAILS)

05:06.907 --> 05:08.640
HE JUMPED IN A CAR.
HE WENT THAT WAY!

05:08.642 --> 05:10.375
LEAH: WHAT KIND OF CAR?
<i> CARLA: I DON' KNOW.</i>

05:10.377 --> 05:11.727
WHITE, A REGULAR CAR.

05:11.728 --> 05:13.078
SPIKE:
YOU SEE A LICENSE PLATE?
CAN YOU DESCRIBE HIM?

05:13.080 --> 05:15.414
CARLA:
UM, A WHITE GUY IN A SUIT.

05:15.416 --> 05:16.415
SPIKE:
WHITE CAR, NO PLATES.

05:16.417 --> 05:18.067
THAT'S NOT A LOT TO GO ON.

05:18.068 --> 05:19.718
HE'S LONG GONE.
LET'S CHECK THE HOUSE.

05:19.720 --> 05:20.819
SAM:
MA'AM, ANY SHOTS FIRED?

05:20.821 --> 05:22.387
UM, WHEN HE CAME OUT
OF THE HOUSE,

05:22.388 --> 05:23.954
<i> HE WENT TO THE GARAGE,</i>
<i> AND THEN IT WOULDN'T OPEN</i>

05:23.957 --> 05:25.407
SO HE SCREWED, UM, A -

05:25.408 --> 05:26.858
WHAT DO YOU CALL IT? -
A SILENCER ON THE GUN,

05:26.860 --> 05:28.794
AND THEN HE STARTED
SHOOTING AT THE LOCK.

05:28.796 --> 05:30.596
WHO LIVES HERE?

05:30.597 --> 05:32.397
A SINGLE GUY, EVAN...
NO, ELLIOT.

05:32.399 --> 05:33.621
<i> WE HARDLY KNOW HIM.</i>

05:33.622 --> 05:34.844
<i> HE'S SUPER-QUIET </i>
<i> AND HE KEEPS TO HIMSELF.</i>

05:34.845 --> 05:36.067
JULES:
SAM, THERE'S A CAR RUNNING
IN HERE!

05:36.070 --> 05:37.770
WAIT HERE.

05:37.771 --> 05:39.471
WINNIE, CALL AN AMBULANCE
AND FIND OUT WHO LIVES HERE!

05:39.473 --> 05:40.472
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> COPY.</i>

05:40.473 --> 05:41.472
JULES:
ELLIOT, ARE YOU IN THERE?!

05:41.475 --> 05:42.507
(SHALLOW BREATHING)

05:42.509 --> 05:44.676
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> ELLIOT, CAN YOU HEAR ME?</i>

05:44.678 --> 05:45.877
(HANDLE BANGS)

05:45.879 --> 05:47.846
JULES: ELLIOT?!
LEAH: ALL CLEAR!

05:49.083 --> 05:52.384
JULES:
BULLET DAMAGED THE LOCK.

05:52.386 --> 05:54.553
SAM:
MA'AM, DO THESE GARAGES
HAVE INSIDE DOORS?

05:54.555 --> 05:55.843
NO.

05:55.844 --> 05:57.132
SAM:
LET'S GRAB THE HALLIGANS.

05:57.133 --> 05:58.421
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> OKAY, EMS IS ON ITS WAY.</i>

05:58.425 --> 05:59.858
<i> HOMEOWNER'S NAME </i>
<i> IS ELLIOT THAINE.</i>

05:59.860 --> 06:01.126
HE'S A SELF-EMPLOYED ACCOUNTANT.

06:01.128 --> 06:03.362
THIS IS JULES CALLAGHAN,
I'M WITH THE POLICE!

06:03.364 --> 06:04.863
WE'RE HERE TO HELP!

06:04.865 --> 06:05.964
<i> YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY!</i>

06:05.966 --> 06:07.399
(LABOURED BREATHING)

06:07.401 --> 06:10.702
<i>WE'RE GONNA GET THIS DOOR OPEN!</i>

06:10.704 --> 06:12.838
GUYS, THIS PLACE IS LIKE
A BLANK SLATE.

06:12.840 --> 06:14.706
NO COLOUR, NO BOOKS,

06:14.708 --> 06:18.009
NOTHING ON THE WALLS,
NO PHOTOS.

06:18.011 --> 06:19.044
HANG ON.

06:20.681 --> 06:21.947
THINK I GOT SOMETHING.

06:21.949 --> 06:23.465
(ELECTRONIC BEEP)

06:23.466 --> 06:24.982
THE MAN WHO BROKE IN,
DID YOU EVER SEEN HIM BEFORE?

06:24.985 --> 06:26.017
NO, HE LOOKED LEGIT.

06:26.019 --> 06:28.470
I MEAN,
HE WAS WEARING A SUIT,

06:28.471 --> 06:30.922
BUT I'VE NEVER SEEN
A VISITOR THERE BEFORE.

06:30.924 --> 06:31.990
LAINIE:
YEAH.

06:33.127 --> 06:34.926
HOLD ON.

06:34.928 --> 06:36.061
PARKER:
YOU THE ONE THAT WAS ATTACKED?

06:36.063 --> 06:37.062
LAINIE SUMMERS

06:37.064 --> 06:38.597
SERGEANT PARKER,
OFFICER LANE.

06:38.599 --> 06:39.732
<i> THE MAN HAD A GUN?</i>

06:39.733 --> 06:40.866
LAINIE: YEAH.
SECURITY GUARD: I GOT CLOSE,

06:40.868 --> 06:42.033
BUT HE GOT INTO A CROWD
OF STUDENTS.

06:42.035 --> 06:43.602
<i> HE'S GONE.</i>

06:43.603 --> 06:45.170
EITHER OF YOU
GET A LOOK AT HIM?

06:45.171 --> 06:46.738
LAINIE:
DARK HAIR, MAYBE SIX FOOT,
DARK CLOTHES.

06:46.740 --> 06:48.039
ED:
ANY IDEA WHERE
HE WAS TAKING YOU?

06:48.041 --> 06:50.776
LAINIE:
NO, I GOT- I GOT LUCKY.
I SAW THE GUARD.

06:50.778 --> 06:52.511
SECURITY GUARD:
SHE DECKED HIM, YOU KNOW,
I JUMPED IN...

06:52.513 --> 06:54.813
LAINIE:
SOME OF THE KIDS HELPED TOO.
I JUST... I DON'T KNOW.

06:54.815 --> 06:56.181
HE DIDN'T LIKE THE ODDS.
HE JUST TOOK OFF.

06:56.183 --> 06:58.784
PARKER:
OKAY, WINNIE,
WE NEED UNI'S ON CAMPUS.

06:58.786 --> 06:59.985
SWEEP GEORGE STREET,
THE QUAD...

06:59.987 --> 07:01.487
<i> WINNIE: COPY.</i>

07:01.488 --> 07:02.988
ED:
WANNA GIVE ME HAND WITH THAT?

07:02.990 --> 07:04.390
PARKER:
MISS SUMMERS...

07:04.391 --> 07:05.791
DOCTOR SUMMERS.
LAINIE'S FINE.

07:05.793 --> 07:08.026
LAINIE, ANY IDEA WHY SOMEONE
WOULD TRY TO ABDUCT YOU

07:08.028 --> 07:09.594
IN BROAD DAYLIGHT?

07:09.596 --> 07:11.930
NO, I HAVE NO IDEA.

07:11.932 --> 07:15.000
(WOOD CRACKS LOUDLY,
DOOR CLATTERS UP)

07:18.972 --> 07:20.806
LEAH:
IT'S OKAY, ELLIOT,
WE GOT YA.

07:20.808 --> 07:22.040
ELLIOT:
NO...

07:22.042 --> 07:23.108
(SIREN WAILS)

07:25.746 --> 07:26.862
EMT:
HOW LONG HAS HE BEEN EXPOSED?

07:26.863 --> 07:27.979
SAM:
MINIMUM TEN MINUTES.

07:27.981 --> 07:29.781
EMT:
HE NEEDS OXYGEN,
NON-RE-BREATHER MASK.

07:29.783 --> 07:31.394
JULES:
ALL RIGHT, ELLIOT,
YOU'RE GONNA BE OKAY?

07:31.395 --> 07:33.006
EMT:
WE NEED TO GET HIM
TO THE HOSPITAL, RUN TESTS.

07:33.007 --> 07:34.618
THAT'S A SERIOUS AMOUNT
OF CARBON MONOXIDE.

07:34.621 --> 07:35.921
JULES:
WINNIE, CALL 52,

07:35.923 --> 07:37.489
GET A DETECTIVE
TO THE HOSPITAL.

07:37.491 --> 07:39.191
WE NEED TO QUESTION HIM
WHEN HE PULLS THROUGH.

07:39.193 --> 07:41.410
COPY.

07:41.411 --> 07:43.628
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i>BOSS, YOUR ATTEMPTED ABDUCTION,</i>
<i> HER NAME'S LAINIE SUMMERS?</i>

07:43.630 --> 07:45.630
PARKER:
YES, SPIKE,
WE'RE WITH HER NOW.

07:45.631 --> 07:47.631
SPIKE:
ELLIOT THAINE LEFT A SUICIDE
MESSAGE ON HIS COMPUTER

07:47.634 --> 07:49.000
AND IT WAS FOR HER.
(ELECTRONIC BEEP)

07:49.002 --> 07:50.869
THIS MESSAGE
IS FOR LAINIE SUMMERS.

07:50.871 --> 07:53.004
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> HE'S APOLOGIZING.</i>
<i> HE'S VISIBLY STRESSED.</i>

07:53.006 --> 07:55.173
HE'S UPSET,
SAYING GOODBYE.

07:56.176 --> 07:58.810
THERE'S JUST NO OTHER WAY,

07:58.812 --> 08:00.712
AND I HOPE YOU CAN UNDERSTAND.

08:00.714 --> 08:01.813
<i> I'M SORRY, LAINIE.</i>

08:01.815 --> 08:04.649
LAINIE,
YOU KNOW AN ELLIOT THAINE?

08:04.651 --> 08:06.301
ELLIOT?
YEAH, OF COURSE.

08:06.302 --> 08:07.952
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> TEAM ONE, WE HAVE</i>
<i> A HIJACKED AMBULANCE,</i>

08:07.955 --> 08:09.988
LANSDOWNE AND DUPONT.

08:09.990 --> 08:11.790
LANSDOWNE AND DUPONT?
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

08:11.792 --> 08:13.058
<i> THAT'S JUST AROUND THE CORNER!</i>

08:13.060 --> 08:14.059
TWO GUNMEN.
(KEYBOARD KEYS CLACK)

08:14.061 --> 08:15.360
IS ONE OF THEM
IN A SUIT?

08:15.361 --> 08:16.660
LEFT THE ATTENDANTS
ON THE SIDE OF THE ROAD

08:16.663 --> 08:17.662
AND TOOK OFF WITH THE PATIENT.

08:17.664 --> 08:18.497
SAM:
IT'S GOTTA BE HIM.

08:18.499 --> 08:19.064
ELLIOT THAINE.

08:19.066 --> 08:20.532
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> YUP.</i>

08:20.533 --> 08:21.999
ED: SAM, FIND THAT AMBULANCE.
<i> SAM: COPY.</i>

08:22.002 --> 08:23.001
HOW DO YOU KNOW ELLIOT?

08:23.003 --> 08:24.135
I'M A NEUROSCIENTIST.

08:24.137 --> 08:25.871
<i> ELLIOT IS A RESEARCH SUBJECT</i>
<i> OF MINE.</i>

08:25.873 --> 08:27.906
HE'S...
HE'S A FRIEND.

08:27.908 --> 08:29.007
WHY WERE YOU
STUDYING HIM?

08:29.009 --> 08:30.208
ELLIOT, IS...

08:30.210 --> 08:32.010
HE'S ONE OF A KIND.

08:32.012 --> 08:33.678
HE HAS A RARE KIND
OF HYPERMNESIA.

08:33.680 --> 08:35.597
HE HAS EXCEPTIONAL MEMORY?

08:35.598 --> 08:37.515
LAINIE:
MORE THAN EXCEPTIONAL,
IT'S PERFECT.

08:37.518 --> 08:38.583
LIMITLESS.

08:39.553 --> 08:41.019
<i> LIKE I SAID, HE'S...</i>

08:41.021 --> 08:43.021
HE'S ONE OF A KIND.

08:43.023 --> 08:44.256
(SIREN WAILS)

08:47.094 --> 08:48.460
<i> JULES: (ECHOING)</i>
<i> ELLIOT, ARE YOU IN THERE?!</i>

08:48.461 --> 08:49.827
<i> LEAH: (ECHOING)</i>
<i> IT'S OKAY, ELLIOT.</i>
<i> WE GOT YA!</i>

08:49.828 --> 08:51.194
<i> JULES: (ECHOING)</i>
<i> ELLIOT, CAN YOU HEAR ME?!</i>

08:51.195 --> 08:52.561
<i> EMT:</i>
<i> WE NEED TO GET HIM</i>
<i> TO THE HOSPITAL, RUN TESTS.</i>

08:52.566 --> 08:54.666
<i> THAT'S A SERIOUS AMOUNT</i>
<i> OF CARBON MONOXIDE.</i>

08:54.668 --> 08:56.101
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> (ECHOING)</i>
<i> ELLIOT!</i>

08:56.103 --> 08:57.936
(SHOCKED GASPS)

08:57.938 --> 08:59.838
(SIREN WAILS)

08:59.840 --> 09:02.307
ELLIOT,
WHAT WERE YOU THINKING?

09:03.877 --> 09:18.823
¶¶¶

09:18.825 --> 09:32.070
¶¶¶

09:38.679 --> 09:41.146
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> OKAY, TEAM, THE AMBULANCE</i>
<i> IS HEADING SOUTH ON LANSDOWNE.</i>

09:41.148 --> 09:43.048
<i> I'VE GOT TRANSIT AND TAXIS</i>
<i> IN ON THE APB,</i>

09:43.050 --> 09:44.816
BUT THE AMBULANCE IS RUNNING
LIGHTS AND SIRENS.

09:44.818 --> 09:45.884
COPY.

09:48.622 --> 09:50.188
MAN:
ARE WE CLEAR?

09:51.959 --> 09:53.325
GOOD.

09:53.326 --> 09:54.692
YOU SEE,
NOTHING'S GONNA HAPPEN TO HER

09:54.693 --> 09:56.059
AS LONG AS
YOU DON'T DISAPPOINT ME.

09:56.063 --> 09:57.128
(NERVOUS INHALE)

09:58.031 --> 09:59.130
(ELECTRONIC BEEP)

10:00.067 --> 10:03.068
(ELECTRONIC BEEP,
PHONE RINGS)

10:03.070 --> 10:05.220
ALL RIGHT, WE'RE GOOD.
JUST MAKE SURE YOU STAND-

10:05.221 --> 10:07.371
<i> AARON:</i>
<i> WE DON'T HAVE HER.</i>
<i> THERE WERE COMPLICATIONS.</i>

10:07.374 --> 10:10.208
YEAH, WELL,
ISN'T THAT A SHAME.

10:11.144 --> 10:14.212
I DON'T THINK IT'S GONNA MAKE
MUCH OF A DIFFERENCE.

10:14.214 --> 10:15.630
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> GUYS, LAKESHORE AND JAMISON,</i>

10:15.631 --> 10:17.047
<i> THE AMBULANCE IS STOPPED</i>
<i> AT THE INTERSECTION.</i>

10:17.050 --> 10:19.184
ALL RIGHT, WINNIE,
LOCK OFF THE TRAFFIC.

10:19.186 --> 10:20.919
LAINIE:
HE TRIED TO KILL HIMSELF?

10:20.921 --> 10:22.954
PARKER:
YEAH, I'M SORRY.
WE KNOW THAT'S HARD TO HEAR,

10:22.956 --> 10:25.223
BUT MAYBE YOU CAN HELP US
UNDERSTAND WHY.

10:25.225 --> 10:27.292
<i> ED:</i>
<i> AND WHY SOMEONE WOULD</i>
<i> WANNA TAKE HIM.</i>

10:28.895 --> 10:31.529
<i> LAINIE:</i>
<i> (SIGHS)</i>

10:31.530 --> 10:34.164
ONE OF THE FIRST TESTS
OF HIS MEMORY, I...

10:34.167 --> 10:37.035
I GAVE HIM THESE PAGES.

10:37.037 --> 10:39.171
MA-NA-BA-FA...

10:39.172 --> 10:41.306
LAINIE:
MEANINGLESS RANDOM SYLLABLES,
FOUR PAGES OF THEM.

10:41.308 --> 10:45.143
I READ THEM TO HIM
AND HE RECITED THEM BACK.

10:45.145 --> 10:46.878
THAT WAS THREE YEARS AGO.

10:46.880 --> 10:48.079
<i> LAST WEEK I ASKED HIM</i>

10:48.080 --> 10:49.279
IF HE STILL REMEMBERED
THE SYLLABLES.

10:49.282 --> 10:51.049
AND HE DID?

10:51.050 --> 10:52.817
<i> LAINIE:</i>
<i>YUP. ALSO THE WEATHER THAT DAY,</i>

10:52.819 --> 10:54.753
WHAT HE'D HAD FOR BREAKFAST,

10:54.755 --> 10:56.121
THAT WE DRANK GINGER TEA

10:56.123 --> 10:58.023
<i> AND I WAS A WEARING</i>
<i> A PEACH-COLOURED SHIRT.</i>

11:02.162 --> 11:03.361
<i> THAT'S HIM.</i>

11:03.363 --> 11:05.096
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> THAT'S QUITE A GIFT.</i>

11:05.098 --> 11:07.265
NOT THE WAY
HE SEES IT.

11:07.267 --> 11:09.100
<i> OUR BRAINS ARE CONDITIONED</i>
<i> TO FORGET SELECTIVELY.</i>

11:09.102 --> 11:11.136
WE FORGET PHYSICAL PAIN,
TRAUMA.

11:11.138 --> 11:12.988
IT'S HOW WE COPE.

11:12.989 --> 11:14.839
WE ALL TAKE THAT FOR GRANTED,
BUT...

11:14.841 --> 11:16.141
<i> ELLIOT DOESN'T HAVE</i>
<i> THAT LUXURY.</i>

11:16.143 --> 11:18.410
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

11:18.411 --> 11:20.678
HE LIVES WITH CONSTANT FLASHES
OF INTRUSIVE MEMORY.

11:20.681 --> 11:22.247
<i> THEY FILL EVERY SECOND</i>
<i> OF HIS DAY.</i>

11:22.249 --> 11:24.182
THEY CAN COME AT ANY TIME.

11:24.184 --> 11:26.117
<i> HE HEARS A CAR HONK;</i>

11:26.119 --> 11:27.986
<i> IT DOESN'T JUST REMIND HIM</i>
<i> OF ONE CAR,</i>

11:27.988 --> 11:30.789
IT REMINDS HIM OF EVERY CAR
HE'S EVER SEEN.

11:30.791 --> 11:33.258
<i> THEY ALL POP INTO HIS HEAD</i>
<i> AND THEY'RE ALL HONKING.</i>

11:33.260 --> 11:34.893
THAT'S WHY HIS HOME
IS NEARLY EMPTY -

11:34.895 --> 11:37.318
THE BLANK WALLS -

11:37.319 --> 11:39.742
SO HE AVOIDS
TOO MUCH STIMULATION?

11:39.743 --> 11:42.166
HE STAYS AWAY FROM SMELLS,
SOUNDS, BRIGHT COLOURS...

11:42.169 --> 11:43.802
PEOPLE.

11:43.804 --> 11:47.072
<i> HE WON'T EVEN OPEN HIS BLINDS</i>
<i> AT HOME.</i>

11:47.074 --> 11:49.307
HE'S TRIED EVERYTHING:
MEDICATION,

11:49.309 --> 11:52.143
MEDITATION, HYPNOTHERAPY.

11:52.145 --> 11:53.478
HE CAN'T CONTROL
WHAT HE REMEMBERS

11:53.480 --> 11:55.797
OR WHAT HE SEES.

11:55.798 --> 11:58.115
ED:
SO THESE MEMORIES ARE TRIGGERED
BY RANDOM, ORDINARY THINGS?

11:59.052 --> 12:00.285
LAINIE:
YUP.

12:00.287 --> 12:02.187
HE HAD A HARD CHILDHOOD.

12:02.189 --> 12:04.856
<i> YEAH, HE FACED A LOT OF LOSS,</i>

12:04.858 --> 12:06.157
AND EVERYTHING
HE'S LIVED THROUGH,

12:06.159 --> 12:09.027
IT'S WITH HIM FROM THE MOMENT
HE OPENS HIS EYES

12:09.029 --> 12:11.296
UNTIL WHEN HE GOES
BACK TO SLEEP.

12:11.298 --> 12:13.098
ALL HE WANTS
IS A LITTLE PEACE.

12:14.267 --> 12:17.302
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> IS THAT WHY HE'S SUICIDAL?</i>

12:17.304 --> 12:19.838
I KNEW THAT ELLIOT
WAS STRUGGLING WITH DEPRESSION,

12:19.840 --> 12:22.407
I JUST... I DIDN'T REALIZE
HOW SERIOUS IT WAS

12:22.409 --> 12:24.275
UNTIL A COUPLE DAYS AGO.

12:25.312 --> 12:27.445
LAINIE:
TEQUILA? SERIOUSLY?

12:27.447 --> 12:29.514
ELLIOT:
YEAH, I READ THAT
IF YOU HAVE ENOUGH

12:29.516 --> 12:32.484
YOU GET A LITTLE NUMB,
YOU DON'T FEEL SO MUCH.

12:32.486 --> 12:34.753
PLAY YOUR CARDS RIGHT,
YOU MIGHT EVEN BLACK OUT.

12:37.023 --> 12:38.022
ELL,
YOU'RE 30-YEARS-OLD

12:38.024 --> 12:39.958
AND YOU'VE NEVER
TRIED TEQUILA?

12:39.960 --> 12:40.859
WHY? HAVE YOU?

12:40.861 --> 12:41.993
OH JEEZ.

12:41.995 --> 12:43.912
(LAUGHS) YEAH?

12:43.913 --> 12:45.830
LAINIE:
THERE WAS A PARTY.
I WAS ABOUT 18-YEARS-OLD.

12:45.832 --> 12:48.299
MY PARENTS WERE
OUT OF TOWN.

12:48.301 --> 12:51.402
IT INVOLVED ME CLIMBING UP
ONTO THE BABY GRAND

12:51.404 --> 12:52.871
AND SINGING SHOW TUNES.

12:52.873 --> 12:53.872
(ELLIOT LAUGHS)

12:53.874 --> 12:56.274
<i> VERY LOUD.</i>

12:56.276 --> 12:58.309
IT WAS GREAT UNTIL
THE PIANO COVER CRACKED

12:58.311 --> 13:00.478
AND I GOT GROUNDED
FOR SIX MONTHS.

13:00.480 --> 13:02.280
I WISH I COULD HAVE
SEEN THAT.

13:02.282 --> 13:04.315
NO, YOU DON'T.
(CHUCKLES)

13:04.317 --> 13:07.085
<i> WHEN I HEARD </i>
<i> HOW MUCH HE WAS HURTING...</i>

13:07.087 --> 13:09.320
I DIDN'T KNOW WHAT TO DO,
YOU KNOW?

13:09.322 --> 13:10.421
I'M...

13:10.423 --> 13:13.191
I'M NOT A THERAPIST,
I'M A RESEARCHER.

13:14.261 --> 13:16.995
SO THIS WAS LAST NIGHT,
AND WHAT HAPPENED?

13:20.233 --> 13:21.332
WELL, AT FIRST,
I THOUGHT IT WAS WORKING,

13:21.334 --> 13:23.201
EVERYTHING SORT OF
SLOWED DOWN.

13:24.304 --> 13:26.204
<i> I DIDN'T "SEE" SO MUCH,</i>

13:26.206 --> 13:28.807
AND THEN THE WHOLE ROOM STARTS
SPINNING AND TIPPING

13:28.809 --> 13:30.141
AND I GOT SICK,

13:32.345 --> 13:35.580
AND THE TASTE
AND THE SMELL AND...

13:37.150 --> 13:38.149
AND NOW THAT'S LOCKED IN.

13:38.151 --> 13:39.284
IT'S ANOTHER THING
LOCKED IN.

13:39.286 --> 13:40.885
IT'S SO STUPID,
LAINIE!

13:41.922 --> 13:43.855
I'M SICK,

13:43.857 --> 13:46.074
I'M IN PAIN,
I NEED TREATMENT,

13:46.075 --> 13:48.292
AND THERE ISN'T ANY
AND THERE NEVER WILL BE...

13:48.295 --> 13:51.229
AND THERE'S NOWHERE SAFE
FOR ME,

13:53.033 --> 13:54.499
NOT EVEN AT HOME.

13:56.603 --> 13:57.869
<i> LAINIE:</i>
<i> I'M A FRIEND...</i>

13:57.871 --> 13:59.070
AND I SHOULD'VE BEEN THERE
FOR HIM.

13:59.072 --> 14:00.305
LAINIE,
DON'T BLAME YOURSELF.

14:00.307 --> 14:01.306
HE MAY BE SUICIDAL,

14:01.308 --> 14:02.340
BUT SOMETHING ELSE
TIPPED HIM

14:02.342 --> 14:04.342
OVER THE EDGE TODAY.

14:04.344 --> 14:06.044
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> WE'RE APPROACHING</i>
<i> THE AMBULANCE.</i>

14:06.046 --> 14:07.111
<i> ED:</i>
<i> COPY THAT.</i>

14:07.113 --> 14:08.179
(SIREN WAILS)

14:12.953 --> 14:14.553
WHY WOULD THEY JUST STOP?

14:14.554 --> 14:16.154
JULES:
THIS IS THE POLICE
STRATEGIC RESPONSE UNIT!

14:16.156 --> 14:17.856
THROW YOUR WEAPONS OUT
OF THE VEHICLE

14:17.858 --> 14:21.960
AND STEP OUT WITH YOUR HANDS
WHERE WE CAN SEE THEM!

14:21.962 --> 14:23.194
LET'S MOVE IN.

14:25.098 --> 14:29.000
JULES:
THIS IS THE POLICE!
COME OUT RIGHT NOW!

14:40.280 --> 14:43.181
SAM:
(QUIETLY)
ON THREE, TWO, ONE.

14:45.418 --> 14:46.985
NO ONE'S IN THERE, ED.

14:46.987 --> 14:48.486
ELLIOT'S NOT IN THE AMBULANCE?

14:48.488 --> 14:51.189
JULES:
NO, THEY LEFT IT
AS A DISTRACTION TO STALL US.

14:51.191 --> 14:53.491
ELLIOT'S LONG GONE.

14:53.493 --> 14:56.027
PARKER:
OKAY, LET'S BREAK THIS DOWN.

14:56.029 --> 14:57.295
WHO BREAKS INTO A HOUSE,

14:57.296 --> 14:58.562
CARJACKS AN AMBULANCE
IN BROAD DAYLIGHT -

14:58.565 --> 14:59.964
GO TO ALL THIS TROUBLE

14:59.966 --> 15:01.432
JUST TO GET THEIR HANDS
ON A...

15:04.170 --> 15:05.236
ON A HUMAN CAMERA?

15:06.172 --> 15:07.822
ELLIOT DREW
THE ROSETTA STONE?

15:07.823 --> 15:09.473
LAINIE:
HE SAW IT AT THE BRITISH MUSEUM
WHEN HE WAS EIGHT.

15:09.476 --> 15:12.343
HE DREW IT FROM MEMORY
WHEN I MET HIM.

15:12.345 --> 15:14.479
THAT'S ANCIENT EGYPTIAN,
DEMOTIC SCRIPT, ANCIENT GREEK.

15:14.481 --> 15:16.281
IT'S A FLAWLESS REPLICA.

15:16.282 --> 15:18.082
PARKER:
SO ELLIOT REMEMBERS WORDS,
NUMBERS, PATTERNS...

15:18.084 --> 15:19.217
<i> LAINIE:</i>
<i> EVERYTHING.</i>

15:19.218 --> 15:20.351
EVEN IN LANGUAGES
HE DOESN'T UNDERSTAND.

15:20.353 --> 15:21.886
SO YOU COULD SEND HIM
SOMEWHERE

15:21.887 --> 15:23.420
AND HE COULD ABSORB
INFORMATION UNDETECTED,

15:23.423 --> 15:25.290
SOMEWHERE YOU COULDN'T
BRING A CAMERA.

15:25.292 --> 15:26.424
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> YOU SAID HE WAS RECLUSIVE.</i>

15:26.426 --> 15:28.059
WHO ELSE WOULD KNOW
HE COULD DO THIS?

15:30.664 --> 15:32.597
OH, WE DID AN INTERVIEW
ON "ENQUIRING MINDS,"

15:32.599 --> 15:34.365
<i> THE TV NEWS MAGAZINE.</i>

15:34.367 --> 15:36.601
THEY FEATURED THIS DRAWING.
I MEAN, IT COULD BE ANYONE.

15:39.306 --> 15:40.605
<i> JAY:</i>
<i> HEY, YOU LOOK GOOD, ELLIOT,</i>

15:40.607 --> 15:43.041
<i> BUT TODAY YOUR NAME</i>
<i> IS GREGORY COOK, OKAY?</i>

15:43.043 --> 15:44.242
<i> NOW, LIKE I SAID,</i>

15:44.244 --> 15:46.077
THEY'RE GONNA SHOW US
THE SECURITY ROOM, OKAY?

15:46.079 --> 15:47.729
I NEED YOU TO STUDY
THE FLOORPLANS

15:47.730 --> 15:49.380
AND MAKE SURE THAT
THEY MATCH THE CAMERA ANGLES.

15:49.382 --> 15:50.640
ALSO, WE'RE GONNA...

15:50.641 --> 15:51.899
<i> WOMAN'S ECHOING VOICE:</i>
<i> ELLIOT, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?</i>

15:51.900 --> 15:53.158
...THE TARGET,
WORK FAST...

15:53.159 --> 15:54.417
<i> MAN'S ECHOING VOICE:</i>
<i> YOU ARE VERY VALUABLE TO ME,</i>
<i> ELLIOT... </i>

15:54.421 --> 15:55.937
(MAN ANSWERS PHONE)

15:55.938 --> 15:57.454
<i> MAN'S ECHOING VOICE:</i>
<i> AND YOU WOULDN'T WANNA KNOW</i>
<i> WHAT HAPPENS </i>

15:57.455 --> 15:58.971
<i> IF YOU TALK TO THE POLICE</i>
<i> ABOUT THIS CONVERSATION. </i>

15:58.972 --> 16:00.488
<i> WOMAN'S ECHOING VOICE:</i>
<i> YOU NEED TO LISTEN TO ME</i>
<i> RIGHT NOW.</i>

16:00.493 --> 16:01.492
<i> WHAT ARE YOU DOING?</i>

16:01.494 --> 16:02.493
I CAN'T.
I DON'T THINK I CAN-

16:02.495 --> 16:04.062
HEY, HEY!

16:04.064 --> 16:05.563
YOU CAN, ELLIOT.

16:05.565 --> 16:07.498
YOU CAN, OKAY?

16:09.202 --> 16:10.435
COME ON, OKAY?

16:20.480 --> 16:22.981
LOOKS LIKE THEY WERE TOO BUSY
TO DISENGAGE THE CAMERAS.

16:24.584 --> 16:26.117
SPIKE:
IT MEANS WE HAVE A REAR
AND AN INSIDE VIEW.

16:26.119 --> 16:27.736
LEAH:
YUP.

16:27.737 --> 16:29.354
SPIKE:
HANG ON, ELLIOT,
WON'T BE LONG.

16:33.526 --> 16:36.027
BARNABY:
BARNABY HOWE,
SENIOR PROJECTS MANAGER.

16:36.029 --> 16:37.312
WE SPOKE ON THE PHONE.

16:37.313 --> 16:38.596
JAY:
YEAH, WE WERE JUST TALKING
TO EACH OTHER

16:38.598 --> 16:40.465
ABOUT HOW GRATEFUL WE ARE
FOR YOUR CO-OPERATION.

16:40.467 --> 16:41.466
BARNABY:
ABSOLUTELY.

16:41.468 --> 16:43.167
KEEP US ON OUR TOES.

16:46.272 --> 16:47.672
GOVERNMENT COMPLIANCE OFFICERS.

16:47.674 --> 16:50.274
WE'VE GOT ANOTHER
SECURITY SPOT-CHECK.

16:50.276 --> 16:51.542
ANY METAL OBJECTS
ON THE TRAY, PLEASE.

16:51.544 --> 16:52.910
JAY:
OH. (METAL CLANKS)

16:52.911 --> 16:54.277
BARNABY:
THIS SCANNER'S
STATE-OF-THE-ART,

16:54.280 --> 16:57.115
PICKS UP EVEN
THE SMALLEST METAL MASS.

16:58.051 --> 16:59.283
(METAL CLINKS)

17:05.592 --> 17:08.426
GUARD:
ARMS OUT.
HOLD STILL, PLEASE.

17:08.428 --> 17:11.596
(HIGH-PITCHED BEEP,
LOW PULSING HUM)

17:12.532 --> 17:14.532
<i> (ELECTRONIC BEEP)</i>
<i> CLEAR. PROCEED.</i>

17:14.534 --> 17:15.666
JAY:
MM-HMM.

17:18.405 --> 17:20.055
<i> GUARD:</i>
<i> PLEASE HOLD STILL, SIR.</i>

17:20.056 --> 17:21.706
(HIGH-PITCHED BEEP,
LOW PULSING HUM)

17:21.708 --> 17:22.740
(ELECTRONIC BEEP)

17:22.742 --> 17:25.176
GUARD:
CLEAR. PROCEED.

17:25.178 --> 17:27.578
<i> BARNABY:</i>
<i> HOWARD, YOU'LL BE OUR ESCORT.</i>

17:27.580 --> 17:28.646
(METAL CLINKS)

17:30.116 --> 17:32.350
SECURITY COMPLIANCE CHECK.

17:36.056 --> 17:37.455
(OVER P.A. SYSTEM)
ATTENTION ALL STAFF.

17:37.457 --> 17:39.590
WE HAVE GOVERNMENT SECURITY
COMPLIANCE OFFICERS

17:39.592 --> 17:41.142
WITH US TODAY.

17:41.143 --> 17:42.693
PLEASE GIVE THEM
YOUR FULL CO-OPERATION.

17:42.695 --> 17:43.761
THANK YOU.

17:45.765 --> 17:47.665
I WON'T CRAMP YOUR STYLE.

17:47.667 --> 17:49.367
CATCH YOU ON THE WAY OUT.

17:49.369 --> 17:50.835
JAY:
APPRECIATE IT.

17:53.073 --> 17:55.173
ELLIOT:
(FAST, SHALLOW BREATHING)

17:58.511 --> 18:00.595
<i> JAY:</i>
<i> UH, GENTLEMEN,</i>
<i> I JUST WANTED TO SAY</i>

18:00.596 --> 18:02.680
<i> WE'VE HAD SOME GRAVE CONCERNS</i>
<i> IN REGARDS TO...</i>

18:02.682 --> 18:04.282
(SOUND DISTORTS)

18:06.152 --> 18:07.718
ELLIOT:
(BREATHING ERRATICALLY)

18:22.535 --> 18:24.502
SPIKE:
HELLO! WE GOT A FACE.

18:24.503 --> 18:26.470
JULES:
WINNIE, SPIKE'S SENDING YOU
A PICTURE OF ELLIOT'S ABDUCTOR.

18:26.473 --> 18:28.290
ANYTHING YOU CAN FIND.

18:28.291 --> 18:30.108
SPIKE:
WE'VE ALSO GOT AN IMAGE
ON THE BUMPER CAM, WINNIE.

18:30.110 --> 18:33.611
THEY SWITCHED INTO A GREY VAN,
MARKER 6-8-9 4-T-M.

18:34.614 --> 18:37.315
OKAY, I'LL RUN THE PHOTO
AND PUT AN APB OUT ON THE VAN.

18:37.317 --> 18:38.649
SAM:
WHAT KIND OF INFORMATION
IS WORTH THE RISK

18:38.651 --> 18:40.034
THESE GUYS ARE TAKING?

18:40.035 --> 18:41.418
SPIKE:
INFORMATION WORTH
A LOT OF MONEY.

18:41.421 --> 18:42.286
WHATTA YOU GOT, BOSS?

18:42.288 --> 18:43.821
OKAY, TEAM,

18:43.822 --> 18:45.355
ELLIOT'S GOT AN EXTRAORDINARY
PHOGRAPHIC MEMORY.

18:45.358 --> 18:47.558
WE'RE THINKING WHERE WOULD
YOU NEED A GUY LIKE THAT?

18:47.560 --> 18:49.327
SPIKE:
YOU CAN GET MICRO-CAMERAS
THE SIZE OF A FRECKLE.

18:49.329 --> 18:51.362
WHY WOULD YOU USE A HUMAN,
AN UNWILLING ONE?

18:51.364 --> 18:53.364
A HUMAN GETS PAST
METAL DETECTORS.

18:53.366 --> 18:54.565
SO SOMEWHERE WITH
TIGHT SECURITY,

18:54.567 --> 18:55.933
NO PHOTOS.

18:55.934 --> 18:57.300
JULES:
MAYBE GOVERNMENT, MILITARY?

18:57.301 --> 18:58.667
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> TEAM ONE, THE LICENCE PLATES</i>
<i> ON THAT VAN</i>

18:58.671 --> 19:00.671
ARE OFFICIALLY BOGUS.
IT'S A DEAD END,

19:00.673 --> 19:02.673
BUT WE DO HAVE A MATCH
ON OUR HIJACKER.

19:02.675 --> 19:04.208
SPIKE:
GO, WINNIE.

19:04.209 --> 19:05.742
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> JAY PENAK.</i>
<i> HE'S ON THE FEDERAL WATCHLIST.</i>

19:05.745 --> 19:07.562
HE'S A FREQUENT FLIER,

19:07.563 --> 19:09.380
ESPECIALLY TO EASTERN EUROPE
AND CHINA.

19:09.382 --> 19:10.615
<i> HE'S WELL-CONNECTED</i>

19:10.616 --> 19:11.849
AND HE'S KNOWN TO HAVE CONTACTS
WITH ARMS DEALERS.

19:11.851 --> 19:13.718
OF COURSE, WEAPONS.

19:22.629 --> 19:23.861
JAY AND HOWARD:
(GRUNTING AND GRAPPLING)

19:23.863 --> 19:25.930
JAY:
DON'T SAY ANYTHING.

19:28.868 --> 19:30.868
<i> COME ON, COME ON.</i>

19:32.839 --> 19:34.756
(VIOLENT BLOW,
HOWARD GRUNTS)

19:34.757 --> 19:36.674
SPIKE:
OKAY, WE GOT THREE PRIVATE
COMPANIES THAT DO RESEARCH

19:36.676 --> 19:39.060
FOR THE DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE:
(ELECTRONIC BEEPS)

19:39.061 --> 19:41.445
A.G.S. LOEB, BREBTECH,
AND MORTON & FLOYD.

19:41.447 --> 19:42.747
<i> WINNIE:</i>
<i> OKAY, I'LL GET UNMARKED CARS</i>
<i> TO ALL THREE,</i>

19:42.749 --> 19:44.815
EYES PEELED FOR THE VAN.

19:48.588 --> 19:49.687
OKAY, THE BLIND SPOT,
THE BLIND SPOT,

19:49.689 --> 19:50.688
WHICH WAY?

19:50.690 --> 19:52.790
UH...

19:52.792 --> 19:55.426
WE GOTTA PASS TWO CAMERAS.
THIRD DOOR ON THE RIGHT...

19:55.428 --> 19:57.528
JAY:
JUST SHOW ME, JUST SHOW ME!
LET'S GO!

19:58.464 --> 20:00.464
GREY VAN'S BEEN SIGHTED
NEAR TOMKEN AND BRITTANIA.

20:00.466 --> 20:01.666
AND THAT'S RIGHT NEAR...?

20:01.668 --> 20:03.635
A.G.S. LOEB.

20:03.636 --> 20:05.603
SAM: LET'S MOVE!
JULES: LET'S DO IT.

20:09.275 --> 20:11.459
(ELECTRONIC BEEPS)

20:11.460 --> 20:13.644
TREVOR:
COME ON IN AND I'LL REVIEW
OUR SECURITY PROTOCOL.

20:13.646 --> 20:15.012
JAY:
OKAY.

20:15.013 --> 20:16.379
TREVOR:
EVERYTHING'S BY THE BOOK.

20:16.382 --> 20:17.782
YOU KNOW THERE WAS THAT
NEAR-BREACH LAST YEAR.

20:17.784 --> 20:19.117
JAY:
YES, WE KNOW.

20:19.118 --> 20:20.451
TREVOR:
WE TIGHTENED EVERYTHING UP.

20:20.453 --> 20:22.753
IT'S IMPOSSIBLE FOR INFORMATION
TO LEAVE THE PREMISES,

20:22.755 --> 20:24.655
<i> PHYSICALLY OR VIRTUALLY.</i>

20:24.657 --> 20:26.724
<i> THERE ARE NO HARD COPIES</i>
<i> OF THE RESEARCH,</i>

20:26.726 --> 20:28.693
NO PORTS IN THE COMPUTERS,

20:28.695 --> 20:31.662
AND THERE'S NO WIRELESS SIGNAL
WITHIN THE FACILITY WALLS.

20:31.664 --> 20:33.497
SO, WE'RE UNHACKABLE.

20:33.499 --> 20:34.632
JAY:
WE KNOW.

20:36.402 --> 20:38.052
THIS SHOULDN'T TAKE LONG.

20:38.053 --> 20:39.703
SPIKE:
THEY HAVE A CONTRACT
WITH THE DEPARTMENT OF DEFENSE

20:39.706 --> 20:41.772
TO BUILD A SMART GUN SYSTEM.

20:41.774 --> 20:42.840
DETAILS ARE CLASSIFIED,

20:42.842 --> 20:44.759
BUT THEY USE
SELF-GUIDED BULLETS.

20:44.760 --> 20:46.677
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> YEAH, THE MILITARY'S BEEN</i>
<i>TESTING PROTOTYPES FOR A WHILE.</i>

20:46.679 --> 20:48.846
THEY GET THIS RIGHT,
IT'S THE PERFECT FIREARM.

20:48.848 --> 20:50.698
MEANING WHAT EXACTLY?

20:50.699 --> 20:52.549
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> MEANING IT WILL HIT</i>
<i> EVERY TARGET EVERY TIME.</i>

20:52.552 --> 20:54.552
MEANING ANYBODY
WHO GETS HIS HANDS ON IT

20:54.554 --> 20:57.021
WILL THINK HE'S AN UNSTOPPABLE
KILLING MACHINE.

20:57.023 --> 20:59.290
JULES:
SO IF TECH LIKE THIS
HITS THE STREET...

20:59.292 --> 21:00.758
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> YOU THINK GANG WARS</i>
<i> ARE BAD NOW?</i>

21:00.760 --> 21:03.361
WAIT UNTIL THEY HAVE
THE FIREPOWER OF AN ARMY.

21:03.363 --> 21:04.862
GREG, IT'S NOT GONNA MATTER
HOW HARD WE TRAIN.

21:04.864 --> 21:07.431
IF WE START GOING UP AGAINST
GUYS WITH THIS KIND OF FORCE...

21:07.433 --> 21:09.767
PARKER:
I KNOW, EDDIE,
LET'S MOVE!

21:09.769 --> 21:11.836
(RAPID ELECTRONIC BEEPS)

21:15.575 --> 21:17.375
(ELECTRONIC WHOOSHES)

21:19.779 --> 21:20.978
(SOUND DISTORTS)

21:21.814 --> 21:23.814
<i> ED:</i>
<i> MR HOWE, THIS IS ED LANE, SRU.</i>

21:23.816 --> 21:25.783
SIR, WE BELIEVE THERE
ARE UNAUTHORIZED PERSONNEL

21:25.785 --> 21:27.585
<i> ON YOUR PREMISES</i>

21:27.586 --> 21:29.386
<i> LOOKING TO ACCESS</i>
<i> CLASSIFIED INFORMATION.</i>

21:29.389 --> 21:30.421
THAT'S NOT POSSIBLE.

21:30.423 --> 21:31.973
SIR, COULD YOU CHECK
YOUR LOGS,

21:31.974 --> 21:33.524
TELL ME IF THERE ARE
ANY UNFAMILIAR PERSONNEL

21:33.526 --> 21:36.027
ENTERING THE FACILITY
WITHIN THE LAST HALF HOUR.

21:36.029 --> 21:37.895
WE HAVE TWO SECURITY
COMPLIANCE INSPECTORS,

21:37.897 --> 21:39.397
<i>BUT THEY WERE FULLY ACCREDITED.</i>

21:39.399 --> 21:40.564
ED:
ARE THEY STILL IN THERE?

21:40.566 --> 21:41.766
<i> BARNABY:</i>
<i> I'LL FIND OUT.</i>

21:41.768 --> 21:43.034
(PHONE BEEPS OFF)

21:44.504 --> 21:45.770
(WALKIE-TALKIE BEEPS)
ONE-ONE-FIVE, COME IN.

21:45.772 --> 21:47.004
(STATIC CRACKLES)

21:47.006 --> 21:49.040
(WALKIE-TALKIE BEEPS)
ONE-ONE-FIVE, PRIORITY!

21:49.042 --> 21:50.308
(WALKIE-TALKIE BEEPS)

21:51.444 --> 21:52.977
(ELECTRONIC WHOOSHES)

21:54.947 --> 21:56.347
(SOUND DISTORTS)

21:57.083 --> 21:58.549
<i> JAY:</i>
<i> HOW'S IT GOING?</i>

21:58.551 --> 22:00.318
ALMOST DONE.

22:00.320 --> 22:01.819
JAY:
THIS IS EVERYTHING, RIGHT?

22:01.821 --> 22:03.988
ALL THE NOTES, TEST RESULTS,
UPDATES?

22:03.990 --> 22:06.057
EVERYTHING,
I SWEAR TO GOD.

22:06.059 --> 22:08.926
SO WHERE DO YOU KEEP
THE PROTOTYPE?

22:08.928 --> 22:10.428
I SAID WHERE?

22:10.430 --> 22:11.529
IN THE LOCKUP.

22:11.531 --> 22:12.596
SHOW ME.

22:14.000 --> 22:15.366
(ELECTRONIC WHOOSHES)

22:15.368 --> 22:16.500
(SIRENS WAIL)

22:21.040 --> 22:22.606
(SIRENS CUT OFF)

22:22.608 --> 22:23.741
ED,
SAM, JULES, WE'RE GOING IN.

22:23.743 --> 22:25.409
KEEP YOUR EYES OPEN
FOR THE VAN.

22:25.411 --> 22:26.844
SAM:
COPY.

22:26.846 --> 22:28.329
ED:
WHAT'S GOIN' ON?

22:28.330 --> 22:29.813
MY ESCORT'S NOT RESPONDING.
THEY MAY HAVE HIS GUN!

22:29.816 --> 22:30.881
OKAY.

22:45.565 --> 22:46.564
AMMO?

22:46.566 --> 22:47.565
ED:
WHICH WAY?

22:47.567 --> 22:48.750
BARNABY:
HERE.

22:48.751 --> 22:49.934
PARKER:
IS THERE A PHONE
IN THAT ROOM?

22:49.936 --> 22:50.968
BARNABY:
YEAH, HARD-WIRED.

22:50.970 --> 22:52.937
PARKER:
CALL IT, PLEASE.

22:52.939 --> 22:54.472
(PHONE KEYS BEEP)

22:55.141 --> 22:57.675
JAY:
I WANT YOU TO SHOW ME
HOW THIS WORKS.

22:57.677 --> 22:58.943
(TELEPHONE RINGS)

23:03.549 --> 23:04.915
(GUN CLICKS)
TELL ME HOW THIS WORKS.

23:04.917 --> 23:05.916
TREVOR:
UH...

23:05.918 --> 23:07.118
TELL ME.

23:07.120 --> 23:08.719
YOU GET A LOCK
ON YOUR TARGET

23:08.721 --> 23:09.854
WITH THE LASER SIGHT.

23:09.856 --> 23:11.589
<i>IT CHARTS A PATH</i>
<i>FOR THE BULLET,</i>

23:11.591 --> 23:13.457
THE BULLET AUTO-CORRECTS
IN FLIGHT.

23:13.459 --> 23:14.992
BARNABY:
NO ANSWER.

23:14.994 --> 23:17.061
JAY:
WHAT IF MY TARGET'S
BEHIND COVER?

23:17.063 --> 23:20.030
YOU TAKE YOUR READING
FROM THE OBSTRUCTION,

23:20.032 --> 23:22.433
MANUALLY ADJUST THE DISTANCE
ONE YARD OR TWO.

23:22.435 --> 23:24.502
YOU ADJUST YOUR POSITION,

23:24.504 --> 23:26.036
THE GUN MEASURES
THE CHANGE OF ANGLE

23:26.038 --> 23:27.972
<i> BASED ON THE ORIGINAL</i>
<i> LASER READING.</i>

23:27.974 --> 23:31.175
<i> YOU FIRE,</i>
<i> THE BULLET CORRECTS ITS PATH,</i>

23:31.177 --> 23:34.478
<i> YOU HIT THE TARGET </i>
<i> BEHIND THE OBSTRUCTION.</i>

23:34.480 --> 23:35.679
(LAUGHS)

23:35.681 --> 23:37.415
I GOTTA TELL YA,
THAT'S SOMETHING ELSE.

23:37.417 --> 23:38.582
(LAUGHS)

23:38.584 --> 23:39.650
ARE YOU DONE,
ELLIOT?

23:41.587 --> 23:42.653
ELLIOT!

23:43.623 --> 23:45.556
I'M DONE.

23:45.558 --> 23:48.526
JAY:
THIS IS YOUR BRAIN CHILD, HUH?

23:48.528 --> 23:50.995
NO ONE KNOWS THIS STUFF
LIKE YOU?

23:50.997 --> 23:52.696
THAT'S RIGHT.

23:52.698 --> 23:53.531
THAT'S GOOD.

23:53.533 --> 23:54.532
(GUNSHOT BOOMS)

23:54.534 --> 23:55.699
ELLIOT:
(GASPS)

23:55.701 --> 23:58.002
ED:
SHOT FIRED!
GO, GO, GO!

23:58.004 --> 23:59.837
JAY:
LET'S GO.

23:59.839 --> 24:00.838
NOW!

24:00.840 --> 24:02.840
<i> OR LAINIE'S NEXT!</i>

24:13.820 --> 24:15.803
BARNABY:
TREVOR WAS OUR LEAD RESEARCHER.

24:15.804 --> 24:17.787
SPIKE:
THIS IS HOW JAY PENAK
DEALS WITH COMPETITION?

24:17.790 --> 24:20.191
WHERE ARE YOUR WEAPONS KEPT?

24:22.995 --> 24:24.462
(ELECTRONIC BEEPS)

24:26.165 --> 24:28.632
HE'S GOT THE XC-2 PROTOTYPE.

24:28.634 --> 24:29.934
PARKER:
SILVER LINING -
ELLIOT'S SAFE.

24:29.936 --> 24:31.602
AS LONG AS HE'S GOT
THOSE SCHEMATICS,

24:31.604 --> 24:32.803
THEY WON'T LET ANYTHING
HAPPEN TO HIM.

24:32.805 --> 24:33.904
YEAH, BUT NOW THEY'LL DO
WHATEVER IT TAKES

24:33.906 --> 24:35.072
TO GET HIM
TO THE FINISH LINE.

24:35.074 --> 24:36.424
ED:
SPIKE, LET'S GET EYES.

24:36.425 --> 24:37.775
WE GOTTA GET 'EM
BEFORE THEY LEAVE THE BUILDING.

24:37.777 --> 24:39.043
YOUR SECURITY,
WHICH WAY?

24:39.045 --> 24:40.110
FOLLOW ME.

24:43.182 --> 24:44.782
SPIKE:
NO ONE SAW THEM ENTER
THE SECURE ROOM

24:44.784 --> 24:46.116
OR ACCESS THE RESEARCH?

24:46.118 --> 24:47.818
NO CAMERAS IN THAT ROOM.

24:51.057 --> 24:51.906
SECURITY REASONS.

24:51.907 --> 24:52.756
DID THEY GET ACCESS
TO THE FACILITY'S FLOORPLANS

24:52.758 --> 24:54.625
OR THE CCTV SYSTEM?

24:54.627 --> 24:56.026
THE SECURITY ROOM
WAS THEIR FIRST STOP.

24:56.028 --> 24:57.795
SPIKE:
GUYS, ELLIOT SAW THE FLOORPLAN.

24:57.797 --> 24:59.074
THEY GOT AN ADVANTAGE.

24:59.075 --> 25:00.352
THEY'RE GONNA KNOW
EVERY SQUARE INCH OF THIS PLACE.

25:00.353 --> 25:01.630
WELL, AT LEAST THEY CAN'T
GET THE SCHEMATICS

25:01.634 --> 25:03.584
OUT OF THE BUILDING.

25:03.585 --> 25:05.535
ACTUALLY, THEY CAN.
LONG STORY.

25:05.538 --> 25:07.872
ED:
THEY'RE GONNA AVOID THE CAMERAS
IN THE MAIN HALLWAYS.

25:07.874 --> 25:09.573
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SPIKE, WHAT ABOUT</i>
<i> SERVICE CORRIDORS?</i>

25:09.575 --> 25:11.575
SPIKE:
YEAH, I WAS JUST THINKING
THE SAME THING.

25:11.576 --> 25:13.576
BOSS, YOU GO STRAIGHT AHEAD,
YOU TURN LEFT.

25:13.579 --> 25:14.845
<i> LEAH: (OVER P.A.)</i>
<i> ATTENTION ALL EMPLOYEES.</i>

25:14.847 --> 25:16.947
THIS IS
THE STRATEGIC RESPONSE UNIT.

25:16.949 --> 25:18.816
<i> PLEASE LEAVE ALL OPEN AREAS</i>
<i> IMMEDIATELY.</i>

25:18.818 --> 25:20.273
JAY:
DAMN IT! LET'S GO!

25:20.274 --> 25:21.729
<i> LEAH: (OVER P.A.)</i>
<i> REMAIN BEHIND LOCKED DOORS</i>

25:21.730 --> 25:23.185
<i> UNTIL WE GIVE YOU</i>
<i> THE ALL-CLEAR.</i>

25:23.189 --> 25:25.556
OKAY, THIS FACILITY'S
GOT FOUR EXITS.

25:25.558 --> 25:27.658
<i> YOU GOT TWO EXITS</i>
<i> ON THE SOUTH SIDE.</i>

25:27.660 --> 25:30.127
LEAH:
SO ELLIOT AND JAY,
THEY'RE HEADED HERE OR HERE.

25:30.129 --> 25:32.563
SPIKE:
ED, SERVICE CORRIDOR C.

25:32.565 --> 25:34.965
WE DON'T KNOW IF HE'S GOING
TO THE EAST OR THE WEST EXIT.

25:34.967 --> 25:37.435
I'LL BACK YOU UP.

25:37.436 --> 25:39.904
<i> ED:</i>
<i> LEAH, WEST EXIT WITH THE BOSS.</i>
<i> I'LL TAKE THE EAST.</i>

25:39.906 --> 25:40.905
ELLIOT:
BUT THE POLICE ARE-

25:40.907 --> 25:42.072
JAY:
JUST KEEP MOVIN'!

25:42.074 --> 25:43.140
WHICH WAY?

25:45.211 --> 25:46.277
COME ON!

25:53.619 --> 25:56.186
ELLIOT:
(PANICKED BREATHING)

25:56.188 --> 25:57.254
WHICH WAY?

25:58.791 --> 26:00.190
WHICH WAY?

26:01.727 --> 26:04.962
(BOOMING GUNSHOT,
DISTORTED CRACKLES)

26:07.133 --> 26:08.198
I CAN'T DO THIS ANYMORE.

26:08.200 --> 26:09.900
JAY:
EAST EXIT.
WHICH WAY?

26:09.902 --> 26:11.385
I'M SORRY,
I CAN'T SEE IT.

26:11.386 --> 26:12.869
JAY:
YOU START SEEIN' IT
OR LAINIE SUMMERS IS GONNA DIE,

26:12.872 --> 26:14.572
<i> DO YOU HEAR ME?</i>

26:14.574 --> 26:16.106
(SOUND DISTORTS)

26:16.108 --> 26:17.775
<i> WOMAN'S ECHOING VOICE:</i>
<i> (LAUGHING)</i>

26:17.777 --> 26:20.411
EAST EXIT!

26:20.412 --> 26:23.046
<i> WOMAN'S ECHOING VOICE:</i>
<i> ELLIOT...</i>
<i> ELLIOT, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?</i>

26:23.049 --> 26:24.348
<i> JAY:</i>
<i> THINK BRANIAC!</i>
<i> COME ON!</i>

26:24.350 --> 26:26.216
<i> FOR GOD SAKE,</i>
<i> WE'RE OUT OF TIME!</i>

26:26.218 --> 26:28.102
<i> FOCUS!</i>

26:28.103 --> 26:29.987
<i> WOMAN'S ECHOING VOICE:</i>
<i> ELLIOT, YOU NEED TO LISTEN</i>
<i> TO ME.</i>

26:29.989 --> 26:32.022
<i> YOU NEED TO LISTEN TO ME</i>
<i> RIGHT NOW.</i>

26:32.024 --> 26:34.158
<i> WHAT ARE YOU DOING?</i>

26:35.761 --> 26:36.760
IT'S THAT WAY.

26:36.762 --> 26:38.796
JAY:
GOOD. OKAY, GO! GO, GO!

26:39.031 --> 26:40.698
SPIKE:
WHAT CAN YOU TELL ME
ABOUT THIS SMART GUN?

26:40.700 --> 26:42.032
WELL, THE BULLET
HAS AN ONBOARD CHIP

26:42.034 --> 26:43.634
AND THE GUN
HAS A LASER SIGHT.

26:43.636 --> 26:45.002
THE GUN TELLS THE BULLET
WHERE TO GO.

26:45.004 --> 26:46.804
BY RADIO SIGNAL.

26:48.007 --> 26:49.106
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> VEHICLE'S APPROACHING</i>
<i> THE DELIVERY DOOR,</i>

26:49.108 --> 26:50.874
BLACK ALPHA TWO.

26:50.876 --> 26:52.009
WE'LL STAND BY TO INTERCEPT.

26:52.011 --> 26:53.944
SPIKE:
THERE. EAST EXIT, ED!

26:53.946 --> 26:55.930
PARKER:
WHICH WAY, SPIKE?

26:55.931 --> 26:57.915
SPIKE:
BOSS, LEAH, YOU GUYS GO
STRAIGHT PAST THE LOADING BAY,

26:57.917 --> 26:59.650
THEN YOU GO LEFT.
ED'S NEARLY THERE!

26:59.652 --> 27:01.685
(QUIETLY) LET'S FLANK HIM.
HE WON'T KNOW WHAT HIT HIM.

27:01.687 --> 27:03.287
PARKER:
COPY. ED, WE'RE RIGHT
BEHIND YOU.

27:03.289 --> 27:04.355
ON MY GO.

27:17.903 --> 27:18.902
HE'S HERE.

27:18.904 --> 27:19.970
(GUN CLICKS)

27:21.340 --> 27:22.806
<i> ELLIOT:</i>
<i>PLEASE DON'T HURT ANYBODY ELSE.</i>

27:22.807 --> 27:24.273
YOU HAVE ME.
YOU HAVE EVERYTHING YOU NEED!

27:24.276 --> 27:26.143
<i> DON'T, PLEASE! PLEASE!</i>

27:26.145 --> 27:27.945
PUT THE WEAPON DOWN!

27:27.947 --> 27:29.146
(DISTORTED BOOM)

27:32.385 --> 27:35.219
(HARD IMPACT,
ED GRUNTS IN PAIN)

27:35.221 --> 27:36.220
(HARD THUMP)

27:36.222 --> 27:37.187
NO.

27:37.189 --> 27:38.255
ED, STATUS.

27:39.358 --> 27:40.424
COME ON.

27:43.829 --> 27:45.796
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SPIKE, CAN YOU GET EYES</i>
<i> IN THERE?</i>

27:45.798 --> 27:47.231
ED'S HIT.
BOSS, I DON'T HAVE A VISUAL!

27:49.301 --> 27:50.701
PARKER:
EDDIE.

27:50.703 --> 27:52.369
COME ON, BUDDY,
TALK TO ME.

27:52.371 --> 27:54.038
ED:
(GRIMACES IN PAIN)

27:54.974 --> 27:56.206
(GUN CLATTERS)

27:59.078 --> 28:01.245
PARKER:
OKAY, JAY,

28:01.247 --> 28:02.680
I'M SERGEANT PARKER
WITH THE POLICE.

28:02.682 --> 28:04.314
I JUST WANT TO KNOW
IF MY GUY'S ALL RIGHT.

28:04.316 --> 28:05.816
JAY:
STEP BACK!

28:05.818 --> 28:06.817
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> (QUIETLY OVER RADIO)</i>
<i> EDDIE.</i>

28:06.819 --> 28:07.951
(GRIMACING)
I'M OKAY.

28:07.953 --> 28:09.086
(RELIEVED SIGH)

28:11.924 --> 28:14.725
JAY:
HEY, STAY CALM
AND CUFF HIM.

28:17.029 --> 28:19.063
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i>SAM, JULES, MOVE IN ON THE VAN.</i>

28:21.734 --> 28:23.701
SAM:
(CCELERATES)
MOVING IN ON THE VAN!

28:23.703 --> 28:24.935
(SIREN CHIRPS)

28:26.272 --> 28:27.404
JULES AND SAM:
POLICE! DROP IT!

28:27.406 --> 28:28.939
DON'T EVEN THINK ABOUT IT!
DROP IT NOW!

28:28.941 --> 28:30.708
ON THE GROUND NOW!
DROP YOUR WEAPON NOW!

28:30.710 --> 28:31.742
HANDS WHERE I CAN SEE THEM!
ON THE GROUND!

28:31.744 --> 28:33.777
JULES:
DROP IT! DROP IT!

28:33.779 --> 28:36.814
HEY, JAY,
YOU GOT WHAT YOU CAME FOR.

28:36.816 --> 28:39.149
NOW ALL I'M ASKING YOU TO DO
IS WALK AWAY FROM THAT OFFICER.

28:39.151 --> 28:40.984
NO, HE'S COMIN' WITH US!

28:40.986 --> 28:42.352
ANYTHING OR ANYBODY
GETS IN THE WAY

28:42.354 --> 28:44.021
AND I'M GONNA KILL HIM!

28:46.258 --> 28:49.226
COME ON, LET'S GET HIM UP!
STAND HIM UP.

28:50.162 --> 28:51.929
YOU'RE GONNA HAVE TO CALL OFF
YOUR REINFORCEMENTS

28:51.931 --> 28:53.047
AND GIVE US CLEAR PASSAGE,
DO YOU HEAR ME?!

28:53.048 --> 28:54.164
ED:
(QUIETLY INTO RADIO)
STAY WITH US, STAY WITH US.

28:54.166 --> 28:55.733
WE'LL FIND A WAY.

28:55.735 --> 28:56.800
(RADIO SQUAWKS)

28:58.804 --> 29:00.938
<i> JAY:</i>
<i> YOU HEAR ME?!</i>

29:00.940 --> 29:04.274
PARKER:
OKAY, TEAM, STAND DOWN. LEAH.

29:04.276 --> 29:07.211
<i> SAM, JULES,</i>
<i> TEAM ONE STAND DOWN.</i>

29:08.147 --> 29:10.448
BOSS, SAY AGAIN?

29:10.449 --> 29:12.750
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> STAND DOWN,</i>
<i> YOU HEARD HIM.</i>

29:14.053 --> 29:15.152
SAM:
YES, SIR.

29:15.154 --> 29:16.887
ALL RIGHT,
YOU'VE GOT CLEAR PASSAGE!

29:16.889 --> 29:19.223
JAY:
LET'S GO!
GET THE DOOR!

29:19.225 --> 29:20.891
(DOOR BANGS OPEN)

29:23.462 --> 29:25.028
PARKER:
ALL RIGHT, LET'S GO.

29:25.030 --> 29:26.096
GO.

29:32.338 --> 29:34.238
AARON:
LET'S GO.

29:34.240 --> 29:36.090
<i> SAM:</i>
<i> WHAT'S THE PLAN, BOSS?</i>

29:36.091 --> 29:37.941
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> THE THREAT TO ED IS REAL.</i>
<i> WE CO-OPERATE FOR NOW.</i>

29:37.943 --> 29:40.944
<i> WE'RE NOT TAKING THAT CHANCE.</i>

29:44.784 --> 29:45.849
ED:
ALL RIGHT!

29:45.851 --> 29:48.152
JAY:
COME ON, GET IN THERE!

29:48.154 --> 29:49.486
<i> LET'S GO!</i>

29:52.491 --> 29:54.324
(VAN STARTS UP)

29:54.326 --> 29:57.261
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SAM, LET'S GET A GPS</i>
<i> ON THAT VAN!</i>

29:57.263 --> 29:58.796
SAM:
I'M ON IT!

30:08.340 --> 30:10.040
(LOUD BOOM AND CLANK,
ELECTRONIC BEEP)

30:10.042 --> 30:11.041
YOU GOT IT!

30:11.043 --> 30:12.242
PARKER:
LET'S GO.

30:18.083 --> 30:19.416
(SIRENS WAIL)

30:19.418 --> 30:21.251
JULES:
THEY'RE FOUR BLOCKS AWAY.
LET'S MOVE!

30:21.253 --> 30:22.486
PARKER:
THE SECOND
THEY SEE US INTERFERE,

30:22.488 --> 30:24.354
WE'VE GOT A SERIOUS RISK TO ED.

30:24.356 --> 30:26.423
SAM:
WE KEEP OUR DISTANCE,
WE PLAN ON THE FLY.

30:26.425 --> 30:27.791
(SIRENS WAIL)

30:27.792 --> 30:29.158
<i> JAY:</i>
<i> PICKED UP SOME COLLATERAL,</i>
<i> BUT NO ONE'S GONNA INTERFERE.</i>

30:29.161 --> 30:30.227
IT'LL WORK.

30:32.164 --> 30:33.163
OH MY GOD.

30:33.165 --> 30:34.565
BREATHE, ELLIOT,
BREATHE.

30:34.566 --> 30:35.966
ELLIOT:
MY GOD, HE'S DEAD,
HE'S DEAD.

30:35.968 --> 30:37.334
JUST BREATHE.
M.

30:37.336 --> 30:38.535
ELLIOT, ELLIOT,
JUST BREATHE-
<i>NO TALKING!</i>

30:38.537 --> 30:40.337
ED:
I'M JUST TRYING
TO CALM HIM DOWN.

30:40.339 --> 30:41.672
YOU HEARD ME.

30:41.673 --> 30:43.006
WHAT'RE YOU GONNA DO?
YOU GONNA SHOOT US?

30:43.007 --> 30:44.340
LET ME JUST TALK TO HIM.
I'M GONNA CALM HIM DOWN.

30:44.343 --> 30:47.211
<i> YOU NEED HIM CALM,</i>
<i> SO LET ME TALK.</i>

30:47.213 --> 30:48.245
ELLIOT,
LISTEN TO ME.

30:48.247 --> 30:49.379
I DIDN'T MEAN FOR THIS
TO HAPPEN.

30:49.381 --> 30:51.215
ALL I WANTED TO DO,
ALL I WANTED WAS-

30:51.217 --> 30:55.085
YOU JUST WANTED TO FORGET.
I UNDERSTAND.

30:55.087 --> 30:56.320
ELLIOT, I KNOW ABOUT
YOUR CONDITION

30:56.322 --> 30:59.957
AND KNOW HOW DIFFICULT
THIS IS FOR YOU.

30:59.959 --> 31:01.458
NOW, SON,
I DON'T HAVE WHAT YOU HAVE,

31:01.460 --> 31:05.028
BUT TELL ME
IF THIS SOUNDS FAMILIAR.

31:05.030 --> 31:07.965
SOMETIMES I'LL BE DOING
SOMETHING ORDINARY

31:07.967 --> 31:11.935
AND FOR NO REASON AT ALL
I SEE SOMETHING

31:11.937 --> 31:15.138
AND I REMEMBER A GIRL
THAT I SAW DIE

31:15.140 --> 31:17.140
AND THE IMAGES FLOOD MY MIND
AND I CAN'T CONTROL IT.

31:17.142 --> 31:18.375
IT JUST HAPPENS,
ELLIOT.

31:18.377 --> 31:20.377
I COULD BE LOOKIN'
AT A COFFEE POT

31:20.379 --> 31:22.179
OR A GOLF BALL...

31:22.181 --> 31:24.081
AND ONE THING JUST FLIPS OVER
INTO THE NEXT THING

31:24.083 --> 31:27.150
AND EVERYTHING TAKES YOU
SOME PLACE YOU DON'T WANNA BE.

31:27.152 --> 31:29.086
AND THE MORE YOU TRY
NOT TO THINK ABOUT IT

31:29.088 --> 31:30.187
THE WORSE IT GETS.

31:30.189 --> 31:33.090
YEAH, YEAH.
EVERYTHING YOU'VE DONE,

31:33.092 --> 31:36.059
EVERYTHING YOU SHOULD
HAVE DONE...

31:36.061 --> 31:38.495
EVERYBODY THAT YOU LOST,
RIGHT?

31:39.431 --> 31:40.497
YEAH.

31:41.433 --> 31:43.467
(CELL PHONE RINGS,
PHONE BEEPS ON)

31:43.469 --> 31:45.636
MARSHALL:
YEAH? WE'RE EN ROUTE.

31:45.638 --> 31:48.338
SO WHAT HAPPENED HERE
WITH THESE GUYS?

31:48.340 --> 31:50.641
ELLIOT:
UH, TWO DAYS AGO,
GUY COMES TO MY DOOR.

31:50.643 --> 31:53.443
HE SAID
HE KNEW A LOT ABOUT ME,

31:53.445 --> 31:55.946
<i> AND HE SAID HE WANTS ME</i>
<i> TO DO A SIMPLE JOB FOR HIM</i>

31:55.948 --> 31:57.414
<i> FOR A CRAZY AMOUNT OF MONEY.</i>

31:57.416 --> 31:59.449
<i> HE DIDN'T TELL ME</i>
<i> WHAT THE JOB WAS.</i>

31:59.451 --> 32:01.051
NO, THANK YOU.

32:01.053 --> 32:02.352
JAY:
ARE YOU SURE?

32:02.354 --> 32:05.022
I MEAN, COME ON, ELLIOT,
THINK ABOUT THE FREEDOM.

32:05.024 --> 32:06.273
YOU TAKE A LONG HOLIDAY

32:06.274 --> 32:07.523
AND VISIT THAT
ROSETTA STONE AGAIN.

32:07.526 --> 32:08.625
NO, THANK YOU.

32:08.627 --> 32:10.193
ALL RIGHT, FINE.

32:10.195 --> 32:11.495
THEN I'LL DOUBLE MY OFFER

32:11.496 --> 32:12.796
AND THAT'LL GIVE YOU A CHANCE
TO BUY BACK

32:12.797 --> 32:14.097
<i> THE OLD FAMILY COTTAGE.</i>

32:14.099 --> 32:15.198
YOU SEE, ELLIOT,
I KNOW YOU.

32:15.200 --> 32:17.501
I'VE DONE MY RESEARCH.

32:18.437 --> 32:21.171
YOU'VE VERY VALUABLE
TO ME, ELLIOT.

32:21.173 --> 32:24.041
(SOUND DISTORTS)
I KNOW LAINIE SUMMERS.

32:24.043 --> 32:28.278
I'M SURE YOU WOULDN'T WANT
TO SEE HER GET HURT.

32:28.280 --> 32:29.646
AND I KNOW YOU'RE NOT GONNA
WANT TO KNOW WHAT HAPPENS

32:29.648 --> 32:33.216
IF YOU TELL THE POLICE
ABOUT THIS CONVERSATION.

32:33.218 --> 32:37.321
<i> ELLIOT:</i>
<i> AND SO HE SAYS HE'S GLAD</i>
<i> THAT I SEE THINGS HIS WAY.</i>

32:37.323 --> 32:38.588
HE SAID HE HAD TO MAKE
PREPARATIONS

32:38.590 --> 32:41.525
AND HE WOULD BE BACK
AT 11 A.M. TODAY TO GET ME.

32:41.527 --> 32:43.493
BY WHICH TIME
YOU'D BE DEAD.

32:43.495 --> 32:46.029
ED, I COULDN'T LET ANYTHING
HAPPEN TO HER.

32:46.031 --> 32:47.197
I WOULDN'T LET THEM
TOUCH HER.

32:47.199 --> 32:48.398
SHE'S THE ONLY ONE
I TRUST WITH EVERYTHING -

32:48.400 --> 32:51.068
THE TRUTH, OKAY?

32:51.070 --> 32:53.070
I WOULD DO ANYTHING
TO KEEP HER SAFE.

32:53.072 --> 32:55.105
YOU KNOW WHAT
I'M REMEMBERING?

32:55.107 --> 32:57.441
I REMEMBER A GIRL
IN A PEACH-COLOURED SHIRT

32:57.443 --> 32:59.743
AND THE TASTE
OF GINGER TEA.

32:59.745 --> 33:01.111
WHAT, YOU MEAN SHE'S,
SHE'S...

33:01.113 --> 33:02.179
SHH...

33:03.182 --> 33:05.115
MARSHALL:
NO, IT'S NOT A PROBLEM.

33:05.117 --> 33:07.084
<i> WE'RE GONNA COVER IT </i>
<i> WITH CASH.</i>

33:07.086 --> 33:08.418
SHE'S ALL RIGHT,
AND I'M PRETTY SURE

33:08.420 --> 33:10.821
SHE'D WANT TO SEE YOU
IN ONE PIECE,

33:10.822 --> 33:13.223
SO HELP ME GET OUT
OF THIS NOW, OKAY?

33:13.225 --> 33:14.524
JUST FOCUS.

33:14.526 --> 33:16.126
(SIRENS WAIL)

33:17.096 --> 33:19.062
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> THEY'RE HEADING NORTHWEST,</i>
<i> CITY LIMITS.</i>

33:19.064 --> 33:20.764
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> IF I WERE JAY</i>
<i> AND MONEY'S NO OBJECT?</i>

33:20.766 --> 33:22.599
I'D TAKE A FLIGHT OUT
UNDER THE RADAR,

33:22.601 --> 33:23.667
TAKE ELLIOT WITH ME,

33:23.669 --> 33:25.386
DOWNLOAD SOMEWHERE SAFE.

33:25.387 --> 33:27.104
SAM:
ANY CHANCE THEY'RE HEADING
TOWARD AN AIRPORT?

33:27.106 --> 33:28.705
JULES:
THEY JUST TOOK A RIGHT.
IF THEY KEEP GOING STRAIGHT

33:28.707 --> 33:30.407
THEY'RE GONNA END UP
IN BUTTONVILLE.

33:30.409 --> 33:32.175
<i> LEAH:</i>
<i> THAT'S A COMMUTER AIRPORT.</i>

33:32.177 --> 33:33.521
PRIVATE FLIGHTS.

33:33.522 --> 33:34.866
THEY CAN PUDDLE-JUMP ANYWHERE
FROM THERE.

33:34.867 --> 33:36.211
JULES:
I'LL MAKE THE CALL.
(CELL PHONE KEYS BEEP)

33:36.215 --> 33:37.347
(SIRENS WAIL)

33:43.789 --> 33:45.222
ED: WHAT'S WRONG?
ELLIOT: (GASPS AND JERKS)

33:45.224 --> 33:46.656
HE'S HAVING A SEIZURE!
HE'S HAVING A SEISURE!

33:46.658 --> 33:48.225
YOU HAVE TO GIVE HIM
HIS MEDICATION!

33:48.227 --> 33:51.228
(HARD PUNCH,
MARSHALL GRUNTS IN PAIN)

33:51.230 --> 33:53.363
DON'T MOVE
AND DON'T TALK!

33:54.299 --> 33:57.367
HELP ME WITH THE CUFFS.
GIVE ME YOUR TIE.

33:58.303 --> 33:59.948
NOT A WORD.

33:59.949 --> 34:01.594
<i> JULES:</i>
<i> I JUST TALKED TO BUTTONVILLE.</i>

34:01.595 --> 34:03.240
THERE'S A PRIVATE PLANE
PERMITTED TO THE AIRFIELD.

34:03.242 --> 34:04.274
<i> IT'S SCHEDULED TO LEAVE</i>
<i> IN TEN MINUTES.</i>

34:04.276 --> 34:06.043
(CELL PHONE RINGS)

34:10.382 --> 34:12.382
<i> SPIKE: SCARLATTI.</i>
ED: SPIKE, IT'S ED.

34:12.384 --> 34:13.650
ED, TALK TO ME.

34:13.652 --> 34:14.902
WHERE ARE WE GOING?

34:14.903 --> 34:16.153
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> PRETTY SURE YOU'RE HEADED</i>
<i> TO BUTTONVILLE</i>

34:16.155 --> 34:17.237
FOR A FLIGHT OUT.

34:17.238 --> 34:18.320
<i> ED:</i>
<i> ALL RIGHT, WE TOOK OUT</i>
<i> THE BABYSITTER.</i>

34:18.323 --> 34:19.656
I GOT HIS GUN.

34:19.658 --> 34:21.124
JAY STILL HAS
THE TRUMP CARD HERE.

34:21.126 --> 34:22.192
WHAT DO WE KNOW?

34:22.194 --> 34:23.427
THE WEAPON THEY TOOK
IS A PROTOTYPE

34:23.429 --> 34:25.295
OF AN EARLIER WORK-IN-PROGRESS.

34:25.297 --> 34:26.696
WE HAVE GOT TO DISABLE
THAT GUN.

34:26.698 --> 34:28.198
ELLIOT:
I'VE GOT THE SPECS.

34:28.200 --> 34:30.133
ED:
THAT'S RIGHT,
YOU DO.

34:30.135 --> 34:31.668
CAN YOU DISABLE IT REMOTELY?

34:31.670 --> 34:33.103
I DON'T KNOW.
I MEAN, IT'S ALL IN MY HEAD,

34:33.105 --> 34:35.272
BUT I DON'T UNDERSTAND
MOST OF IT.

34:35.274 --> 34:36.673
<i> ED:</i>
<i> OKAY, SPIKE,</i>

34:36.675 --> 34:39.309
TALK TO ELLIOT,
SEE IF WE CAN NARROW THIS DOWN.

34:39.311 --> 34:40.811
GO.

34:40.813 --> 34:43.213
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> THE BULLET AND THE GUN</i>
<i> TALK TO EACH OTHER</i>

34:43.215 --> 34:45.232
ON A RADIO FREQUENCY.

34:45.233 --> 34:47.250
WE CAN'T STOP HIM FIRING,
BUT IF WE OVERRIDE THE SIGNAL

34:47.252 --> 34:48.852
WE CAN TAKE THE "SMART"
OUT OF THE BULLET.

34:48.854 --> 34:51.288
OKAY, ELLIOT, ANY REFERENCE
TO RADIO FREQUENCY,

34:51.290 --> 34:52.422
RADIO GUIDANCE?

34:53.392 --> 34:54.458
UH...

34:57.563 --> 34:58.628
UH...

34:59.665 --> 35:00.931
<i> JAY:</i>
<i> ARE YOU SURE?</i>

35:00.932 --> 35:02.198
ELLIOT:
(CRYING) I'M SO SORRY,
LAINIE.

35:02.201 --> 35:03.600
WHAT'S GOING ON,
ELLIOT?

35:03.602 --> 35:05.569
I'M, I'M TRYING.
I'M SORRY, I'M TRYING.

35:05.571 --> 35:07.671
IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY,
YOU CAN DO THIS.

35:07.673 --> 35:10.307
SPIKE:
WE NEED THE SPECIFIC CHANNEL
THAT THE GUN USES

35:10.309 --> 35:12.876
TO COMMUNICATE
WITH THE BULLET.

35:12.878 --> 35:14.277
(SOUND DISTORTS)

35:16.381 --> 35:20.217
<i> "RP-4280/</i>
<i> RESULTS OF PHASE THREE TESTS</i>

35:20.219 --> 35:21.885
<i> TO RADIO GUIDANCE SYSTEM."</i>

35:21.886 --> 35:23.552
ED:
GOOD WORK, GOOD WORK.
SPIKE?

35:23.555 --> 35:26.156
SPIKE:
WE'RE LOOKING FOR A NUMBER,
A MEGAHERTZ RANGE,

35:26.158 --> 35:28.358
SOMEWHERE BETWEEN 100 AND 150.

35:29.294 --> 35:31.394
ELLIOT:
(BREATHES ERRATICALLY)

35:31.897 --> 35:32.896
(SOUND DISTORTS)

35:32.898 --> 35:34.764
I CAN'T SEE IT.

35:34.766 --> 35:37.334
SPIKE:
MAYBE NOT MEGAHERTZ,
MAYBE MHZ.

35:37.336 --> 35:39.169
(SOUND DISTORTS)

35:41.273 --> 35:42.589
UH...

35:42.590 --> 35:43.906
ELLIOT, JUST BREATHE,
SLOW IT RIGHT DOWN.

35:43.909 --> 35:46.843
(EXHALES SLOWLY)

35:46.844 --> 35:49.778
<i> ED:</i>
<i> THAT'S IT, THAT'S IT,</i>
<i> THAT'S IT. YOU GOT IT.</i>

35:51.216 --> 35:52.582
<i> THERE YOU GO.</i>

35:52.584 --> 35:53.884
(SOUND DISTORTS)

35:54.820 --> 35:56.386
<i> ELLIOT:</i>
<i> HERE.</i>

35:56.388 --> 35:58.188
MHZ. 122.8.

35:58.190 --> 36:00.724
THE BULLET RECEIVES ITS SIGNAL
AT 122.8 MHZ.

36:00.726 --> 36:02.792
NICE. SPIKE?

36:02.794 --> 36:05.462
<i> SPIKE:</i>
<i> 122.8, 122.8, 122.8.</i>

36:06.398 --> 36:07.697
ED:
NICE! NICE!

36:07.699 --> 36:09.766
BETTER THAN NICE.
WE SHOULD BE ABLE TO JAM IT

36:09.768 --> 36:11.835
USING A WALKIE
AT THAT FREQUENCY,

36:11.837 --> 36:13.770
USE THE AIRPORT'S ANTENNA
TO BOOST THE SIGNAL.

36:13.772 --> 36:15.906
<i> THE ANTENNA SIGNAL'S </i>
<i>WAY MORE POWERFUL THAN THE GUN.</i>

36:15.908 --> 36:17.697
<i> IT SHOULD OVERRIDE IT</i>

36:17.698 --> 36:19.487
<i> AND MAKE THE BULLET</i>
<i> UNSTEERABLE.</i>

36:19.488 --> 36:21.277
LEAH, WE NEED TO GET WITHIN
40 METRES OF THAT WEAPON.

36:21.280 --> 36:22.279
SPIKE, CAN YOU BE
AT THAT AIRPORT

36:22.281 --> 36:23.313
BEFORE WE ARE?

36:23.315 --> 36:24.915
WE'RE GAINING GROUND.

36:24.917 --> 36:26.383
OKAY, I'M GONNA TRY
AND STALL 'EM.

36:26.384 --> 36:27.850
GET THERE AS SOON AS YOU CAN.

36:27.853 --> 36:29.519
ELLIOT, GOOD WORK.

36:29.521 --> 36:31.354
122.8.

36:31.356 --> 36:33.623
OKAY, EDDIE'S THEIR SAFE PASSAGE
ONTO THAT PLANE.

36:33.625 --> 36:35.525
AFTER THAT...

36:35.527 --> 36:36.593
HE'S DISPOSABLE.

36:44.503 --> 36:45.835
(AIRPLANE HUMS)

36:52.878 --> 36:54.444
AARON:
WHAT DO WE DO
WITH THE COP?

36:54.446 --> 36:55.523
JAY:
WELL, HE'S GONNA KNOW
WE FLEW OUT.

36:55.524 --> 36:56.601
AARON:
HE DOESN'T HAVE TO KNOW WHERE.

36:56.602 --> 36:57.679
JAY:
WELL, THAT'S NOT GONNA HAPPEN.

36:57.683 --> 36:59.083
AARON:
OKAY.

36:59.084 --> 37:00.484
JAY:
WE'RE GONNA GET HIM
ON THIS PLANE

37:00.485 --> 37:01.885
AND DUMP HIM EN ROUTE.
LET'S GO.

37:01.887 --> 37:03.954
ED:
(DOOR BANGS OPEN)
DON'T DO IT!

37:03.956 --> 37:05.455
<i> DON'T DO IT!</i>

37:06.391 --> 37:07.424
YOU'RE NOT GONNA
SHOOT HIM.

37:07.426 --> 37:08.325
YOU THINK I'D EVER
LET THAT GUN

37:08.327 --> 37:10.327
GET OUT ON THE STREET?

37:10.329 --> 37:12.462
YOU THINK I'D EVER,
EVER LET THAT HAPPEN?

37:12.464 --> 37:14.264
BY SHOOTING
AN INNOCENT PERSON?

37:14.266 --> 37:18.335
ONE LIFE FOR THOUSANDS?
THAT'S A NO-BRAINER.

37:18.337 --> 37:19.469
OR WE COULD END THIS
RIGHT HERE.

37:19.471 --> 37:20.670
LOOK AROUND YOU.

37:29.248 --> 37:31.715
KEEP YOUR GUN
ON THE COP.

37:33.418 --> 37:34.651
(SIREN CHIRPS)

37:41.760 --> 37:42.826
(SIREN WHIRS)

37:49.434 --> 37:51.434
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> JAY, I SUGGEST </i>
<i> YOU PUT YOUR GUNS DOWN,</i>

37:51.436 --> 37:53.903
<i> YOU AND YOUR FRIEND!</i>

37:53.905 --> 37:55.705
JAY:
YOU KNOW HOW THIS WORKS,
RIGHT?

37:55.707 --> 37:57.941
THOSE SHIELDS ARE REDUNDANT!

37:57.943 --> 37:59.443
<i> THIS BULLET WILL FIND YOU.</i>

37:59.444 --> 38:00.944
I PULL THIS TRIGGER
AND YOU'RE DEAD!

38:00.946 --> 38:02.979
SPIKE:
NOT IF WE GET THIS RIGHT
HE'S NOT.

38:02.981 --> 38:04.881
JAY:
SO, YOU SEE,
YOU HAVE NO CHOICE.

38:04.883 --> 38:05.982
MATH'S NOT ON YOUR SIDE.

38:05.984 --> 38:08.351
<i> SO HERE'S WHAT'S GONNA HAPPEN:</i>

38:08.353 --> 38:10.754
YOU'RE GONNA LET US GO
OR ONE OF YOU IS GONNA DIE!

38:10.756 --> 38:11.955
THAT'S GUARANTEED!

38:11.957 --> 38:13.590
PARKER:
SPIKE...

38:13.592 --> 38:14.591
ALMOST THERE.

38:14.593 --> 38:16.593
JUST HOOKIN' UP
THE WALKIE.

38:16.595 --> 38:17.594
WE'RE LEAVING.

38:17.596 --> 38:18.595
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> SPIKE. </i>

38:18.597 --> 38:19.780
SPIKE:
KEEP HIM TALKING.

38:19.781 --> 38:20.964
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> OKAY, IF WE PUT</i>
<i> THESE GUNS DOWN,</i>

38:20.966 --> 38:23.500
<i> NO ONE GETS HURT!</i>

38:23.502 --> 38:25.635
(QUIETLY)
WE GOOD, SPIKE?

38:29.007 --> 38:30.840
SPIKE:
WE'RE GOOD, I THINK.
(ELECTRONIC BEEPS)

38:30.842 --> 38:32.542
PARKER:
WHAT DO YOU MEAN
"YOU THINK"?

38:32.544 --> 38:34.077
NO, WE'RE GOOD.

38:34.079 --> 38:35.078
PARKER:
OKAY, SAM, GO!

38:35.080 --> 38:36.880
SAM:
COPY.

38:36.882 --> 38:38.648
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> ALL RIGHT, THAT'S IT!</i>

38:38.650 --> 38:40.600
PUT YOUR WEAPON DOWN!

38:40.601 --> 38:42.551
WHAT DON'T YOU UNDERSTAND?
IF I SHOOT, YOU DIE!

38:42.554 --> 38:45.021
PUT IT DOWN!
PUT IT DOWN NOW!

38:50.562 --> 38:51.928
<i> PARKER:</i>
<i> YOU SEE, JAY?</i>

38:51.930 --> 38:54.531
THE MATH IS NOT ON YOUR SIDE.

38:54.533 --> 38:55.398
LAST CHANCE!

38:55.400 --> 38:57.100
PARKER:
DON'T DO THIS!

39:01.673 --> 39:03.673
(ECHOING GUNSHOT BOOM)

39:07.512 --> 39:09.562
(FIRES GUN)

39:09.563 --> 39:11.613
(DISTORTED WHISTLE
AS BULLET FLIES THROUGH AIR)

39:13.552 --> 39:14.818
(METALLIC BANG)

39:24.429 --> 39:26.763
OKAY, IT'S OVER,
IT'S OVER.

39:26.765 --> 39:27.831
(GUN CLATTERS)

39:27.833 --> 39:29.666
JULES:
HANDS BEHIND YOUR BACK.

39:29.668 --> 39:30.734
STAND UP.

39:35.040 --> 39:37.474
(GURNEY RATTLES ACROSS TARMACK)

39:42.814 --> 39:44.748
LAINIE:
I'M SO SORRY!

39:44.750 --> 39:46.233
ELLIOT:
LAINIE.

39:46.234 --> 39:47.717
I THOUGHT I KNEW
WHAT IT WAS LIKE FOR YOU.

39:47.719 --> 39:49.419
I THOUGHT I UNDERSTOOD.

39:50.155 --> 39:52.589
I ALMOST LOST YOU, ELLIOT.

39:55.827 --> 39:57.627
<i> ED:</i>
<i> YOU SHOULD HAVE</i>
<i> SEEN THIS GUY.</i>

39:57.629 --> 39:59.179
HE COULDN'T LEAVE HIS HOUSE
A WEEK AGO.

39:59.180 --> 40:00.730
HE WAS ABLE TO CUT THROUGH
ALL THAT CHAOS

40:00.732 --> 40:02.415
AND FIND THE ONE TINY PIECE

40:02.416 --> 40:04.099
OF LIFE-SAVING INFORMATION
WE NEEDED.

40:04.102 --> 40:05.702
122.8 MEGAHERTZ.

40:07.706 --> 40:09.973
YEAH, I CLEARED MY MIND.
I DIDN'T HAVE A CHOICE.

40:09.975 --> 40:12.075
THAT'S AMAZING,
ELLIOT.

40:12.077 --> 40:14.144
THAT'S A BEGINNING.
YOU SEE THAT, RIGHT?

40:14.146 --> 40:15.478
YEAH.

